If a bit is set (1), a change of state on the corresponding input triggers a transmission. If the bit is not set (0), no transmission takes place. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Digital inputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryTcpClientInterval.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryTcpClientInterval
wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryTcpClientInterval.description: Configurable interval with a 100ms base, in which the Webio device sends data to the configured application. A interval of zero stopps the periodical sending.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryTcpClientApplicatio.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryTcpClientApplicationMode
wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryTcpClientApplicatio.description: Selection of the application mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : Box2Box Slave Bit 1 : Compatible 50xxx Bit 0 : Default

wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryUdpPeerLocalPort.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryUdpPeerLocalPort
wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryUdpPeerLocalPort.description: Local UDP port for data exchange in this peer to peer mode. This port number must be unique within the device. Reserved port number must not be used (refere to the manual).

wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryUdpPeerRemotePort.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryUdpPeerRemotePort
wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryUdpPeerRemotePort.description: Port number of the remote device. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the remote port to zero.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryUdpPeerRemoteIpAddr.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryUdpPeerRemoteIpAddr
wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryUdpPeerRemoteIpAddr.description: Ip address of the remote device. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the remote device IP address to 0.0.0.0.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryUdpPeerInputTrigger.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryUdpPeerInputTrigger
wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryUdpPeerInputTrigger.description: Every change on the inputs causes their state to be transmitted to the remote device. To minimize data traffic, individual inputs may be exempted from this rule. Nevertheless every transmission will contain all input bits. If a bit is set (1), a change of state on the corresponding input triggers a transmission. If the bit is not set (0), no transmission takes place. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Digital inputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryUdpPeerInterval.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryUdpPeerInterval
wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryUdpPeerInterval.description: Configurable interval with a 100ms base, in which the Webio device sends data to the configured remote device. A interval of zero stopps the periodical sending.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryUdpPeerApplicationM.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryUdpPeerApplicationMode
wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryUdpPeerApplicationM.description: Selection of the application mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : Box2Box Slave Bit 1 : Compatible 50xxx Bit 0 : Default

wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryConnectedPort.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryConnectedPort
wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryConnectedPort.description: Port number of the remote device, after connection has been established. In case of no connection or missing port informations a zero will be read.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryConnectedIpAddr.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryConnectedIpAddr
wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryConnectedIpAddr.description: IP address of the remote device, after connection has been established. In case of no connection or missing port informations 0.0.0.0 will be read.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryTcpServerClientHttp.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryTcpServerClientHttpPort
wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryTcpServerClientHttp.description: HTTP port number of the remote device at TCP Server Mode. If an mailfunction occurs status informations will be send to this port. Not used at mode Compatible 50xxx.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryTcpClientServerHttp.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryTcpClientServerHttpPort
wtWebioEA2x2ERPBinaryTcpClientServerHttp.description: HTTP port number of the remote device at TCP Client Mode. In the operating mode Box2Box connection status informations will be exchanged through this port.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPSyslogServerIP.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPSyslogServerIP
wtWebioEA2x2ERPSyslogServerIP.description: Name or IP address of the Syslog server, which accepts the Syslog messgaes.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPSyslogServerPort.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPSyslogServerPort
wtWebioEA2x2ERPSyslogServerPort.description: Portnumber of the Syslog servers, default 514.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPSyslogSystemMessagesEnabl.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPSyslogSystemMessagesEnable
wtWebioEA2x2ERPSyslogSystemMessagesEnabl.description: Binary coded trigger conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: ColdStart Bit 1: WarmStart Bit 2: Diag Messages Bit 3-7: unused

wtWebioEA2x2ERPSyslogEnable.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPSyslogEnable
wtWebioEA2x2ERPSyslogEnable.description: Set bit 0to enable Syslog: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Syslog enable

wtWebioEA2x2ERPFTPServerIP.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPFTPServerIP
wtWebioEA2x2ERPFTPServerIP.description: Name or IP address of the FTP server, which accepts the FTP messages.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPFTPServerControlPort.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPFTPServerControlPort
wtWebioEA2x2ERPFTPServerControlPort.description: Portnumber of the control port of the FTP server, default 21.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPFTPOption.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPFTPOption
wtWebioEA2x2ERPFTPOption.description: Bit 0 switches the FTP Server in Passiv-Mode, the Client controls the data connection on its own: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : PASV enable

wtWebioEA2x2ERPFTPEnable.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPFTPEnable
wtWebioEA2x2ERPFTPEnable.description: Set Bit 0 to enable FTP: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : FTP enable

wtWebioEA2x2ERPWayBackEnable.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPWayBackEnable
wtWebioEA2x2ERPWayBackEnable.description: Set Bit 0 to enable WayBack: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : WayBack enable

wtWebioEA2x2ERPWayBackServerControlPort.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPWayBackServerControlPort
wtWebioEA2x2ERPWayBackServerControlPort.description: Portnumber of the control port of the FTP server, default 21.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPWayBackFTPPassword.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPWayBackFTPPassword
wtWebioEA2x2ERPWayBackFTPPassword.description: WayBack FTP Loggin: Password of the user.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPWayBackFTPResponse.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPWayBackFTPResponse
wtWebioEA2x2ERPWayBackFTPResponse.description: WayBack FTP response: return message after login.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPWayBackFTPTimeOut.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPWayBackFTPTimeOut
wtWebioEA2x2ERPWayBackFTPTimeOut.description: WayBack FTP Timeout: a request must be finished within this periode of time.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPOutputModeTable.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPOutputModeTable
wtWebioEA2x2ERPOutputModeTable.description: Table of output mode configurations dependent on the output indices.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPOutputModeEntry.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPOutputModeEntry
wtWebioEA2x2ERPOutputModeEntry.description: Output mode configurations of the individual outputs.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPOutputModeBit.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPOutputModeBit
wtWebioEA2x2ERPOutputModeBit.description: This binary coded output mode defines the individual operation mode for any output. More than one mode must not be selected. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 6-7: unused Bit 5 : Logic Bit 4 : Binary 2 Bit 3 : Binary 1 Bit 2 : SNMP Bit 1 : UDP ASCII Bit 0 : HTTP

wtWebioEA2x2ERPSafetyTimeout.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPSafetyTimeout
wtWebioEA2x2ERPSafetyTimeout.description: After this period of time (multiple of 100ms) without receiving data outputs switch to their Safety States. For each output a independend safety state could be defined.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPLoadControlEnable.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPLoadControlEnable
wtWebioEA2x2ERPLoadControlEnable.description: Here the function of automatic load control can be enabled. All output were tested in pairs (0-1). If an error occours at one output, both output of an pair will be switched of. For a properly function of the load control each output of a pair have to has a load. If there is no existing load, a pull down resistor can be used. Outputs with no load are automaticly detected and not part of the control function. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Load Control enable

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmTable.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmTable
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmTable.description: List of settings depending on the alarm number.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmEntry.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmEntry
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmEntry.description: Alarm parameters of the individual alarms.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmInputTrigger.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmInputTrigger
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmInputTrigger.description: This variable allows setting of individual input trigger conditions. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. The first four OCTETS contain the mask which determines which of the inputs are to be considered (corresponding bit = 1) and which inputs are to ignore (corresponding bit = 0): OCTET 1 : unused OCTET 2 : unused OCTET 3 : unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Mask for digital inputs 0-1 OCTETS 5-8 contain the level (1=HIGH, 0=LOW) which the inputs should assume: OCTET 5 : unused OCTET 6 : unused OCTET 7 : unused OCTET 8, Bit 0-1: Level of digital inputs 0-1 OCTETS 9-12 contain the ANY bit (1=ON, 0=OFF). Inputs masked with the any bit trigger with any change of the corresponding input bit. Settings in OCTET 5-9 are then unused: OCTET 9: unused OCTET 10: unused OCTET 11: unused OCTET 12, Bit 0-1: ANY bits of digital inputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmOutputTrigger.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmOutputTrigger
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmOutputTrigger.description: This variable allows setting of individual output trigger conditions. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. The first four OCTETS contain the mask which determines which of the outputs are to be considered (corresponding bit = 1) and which outputs are to ignore (corresponding bit = 0): OCTET 1 : unused OCTET 2 : unused OCTET 3 : unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Mask for digital outputs 0-1 OCTETS 5-8 contain the level (1=HIGH, 0=LOW) which the outputs should assume: OCTET 5 : unused OCTET 6 : unused OCTET 7 : unused OCTET 8, Bit 0-1: Level of digital outputs 0-1 OCTETS 9-12 contain the ANY bit (1=ON, 0=OFF). Outputs masked with the any bit trigger with any change of the corresponding output bit. Settings in OCTET 5-9 are then unused: OCTET 9: unused OCTET 10: unused OCTET 11: unused OCTET 12, Bit 0-1: ANY bits of digital outputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSystemTrigger.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSystemTrigger
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSystemTrigger.description: Binary coded trigger conditions: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 4-7: unused Bit 3 : Warm Start Bit 2 : Cold Start Bit 1 : Timer Bit 0 : Load Control

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmMaxCounterValue.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmMaxCounterValue
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmMaxCounterValue.description: This variable configures a max. counter value. If an input counter value exceeds this max. value, the corresponding alarm is triggered. Input counters with its mask bit unset in wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmInputTrigger are not considered.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmEnable.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmEnable
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmEnable.description: Binary coded alarm enable: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: Mail Enable Bit 1: SNMP Trap enable Bit 2: UDP enable Bit 3: Send inputs to pending TCP connections Bit 4: TCP Client enable Bit 5: Syslog Messages enable Bit 6-7: unused

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmMailAddr.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmMailAddr
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmMailAddr.description: E-Mail address for sending the alarm mail to.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmMailText.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmMailText
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmMailText.description: Alarm mail text: States of the Webio device can be included by using special tags. Please refer to the respective Webio manual

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSnmpManagerIP.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSnmpManagerIP
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSnmpManagerIP.description: IP address of the SNMP Manager to which the Webio device should send SNMP traps.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSnmpTrapText.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSnmpTrapText
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSnmpTrapText.description: This text appears in the trap body.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmUdpIpAddr.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmUdpIpAddr
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmUdpIpAddr.description: IP address of the UDP listener to which the Webio device should send UDP traps.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmUdpPort.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmUdpPort
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmUdpPort.description: Port number of the UDP listener to which the Webio device should send UDP traps.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmUdpText.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmUdpText
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmUdpText.description: This text appears in the UDP trap body.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmTcpIpAddr.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmTcpIpAddr
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmTcpIpAddr.description: IP address of the TCP listener to which the Webio device should send TCP traps.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmTcpPort.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmTcpPort
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmTcpPort.description: Port number of the TCP listener to which the Webio device should send TCP traps.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmTcpText.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmTcpText
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmTcpText.description: This text appears in the TCP trap body.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSyslogIpAddr.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSyslogIpAddr
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSyslogIpAddr.description: IP address of the syslog server to which the Webio device should send syslog messages.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSyslogPort.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSyslogPort
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSyslogPort.description: Port number of the syslog server to which the Webio device should send syslog messages.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSyslogText.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSyslogText
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSyslogText.description: Every message starts with the priority key, a time stamp and the host ip address, according RFC3164. This text appears in the following syslog message body.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmFtpDataPort.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmFtpDataPort
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmFtpDataPort.description: Local data port: 1..65535 or AUTO: the next free port will be assigned.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmFtpFileName.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmFtpFileName
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmFtpFileName.description: Name of the file including path informations.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmFtpText.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmFtpText
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmFtpText.description: Message text to store on the FTP server.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmFtpOption.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmFtpOption
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmFtpOption.description: Binary coded options, select only one option at the same time: STORE = replace file APPEND = append message at the end of the file Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0 : STORE Bit 1 : APPEND Bit 2-7: unused

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmTimerCron.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmTimerCron
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmTimerCron.description: This entry contains 5 space or tab seperated text fields for time trigger definition. Each field must match with the actual time to trigger a message, weekday and day of month are interpreted separatley. 1: Minutes Range 0-59 2. Hours Range 0-23, 0 is midnight 3: Day of month Range 1-31 4: Month Range 1-12 5: Weekday Range 0-6, 0 is sunday Syntax for every field: - an asterix (*) enables every possible setting of a field - single numbers seperated by commas - a partition within the allowed range (1-5) - step size within an partition of the allowed range (0-59/2: every second minute).

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmMailReleaseText.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmMailReleaseText
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmMailReleaseText.description: Release Alarm mail text: States of the Webio device can be included by using special tags. Please refer to the respective Webio manual

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSnmpTrapReleaseText.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSnmpTrapReleaseText
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSnmpTrapReleaseText.description: This text appears in the trap body.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmUdpReleaseText.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmUdpReleaseText
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmUdpReleaseText.description: This text appears in the UDP trap body.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmTcpReleaseText.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmTcpReleaseText
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmTcpReleaseText.description: This text appears in the TCP trap body.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSyslogReleaseText.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSyslogReleaseText
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmSyslogReleaseText.description: Every message starts with the priority key, a time stamp and the host ip address, according RFC3164. This text appears in the following syslog message body.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmFtpReleaseText.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmFtpReleaseText
wtWebioEA2x2ERPAlarmFtpReleaseText.description: Message text to store on the FTP server.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPLoadControlView.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPLoadControlView
wtWebioEA2x2ERPLoadControlView.description: Here the result of automatic load control can be read. All output were tested in pairs (0-1). If an error occours at one output, both output of an pair will be switched of. For a properly function of the load control each output of a pair have to has a load. If there is no existing load, a pull down resistor can be used. Outputs with no load are automaticly detected and not part of the control function. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0-1: outputs 0-1.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPLCShutDownView.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPLCShutDownView
wtWebioEA2x2ERPLCShutDownView.description: Here the result of the automatic load control shut down can be read. All outputs remain switched of, until a zero is written into this variable. But previously all loads should be inspected. High current (short circuit), a broken supply line or a defect load (i.e. lamp) may be a shut down reason. If no load is detected, the load control unit suspend automaticly the control of the corresponding output pair. All controlled output could be identified reading the variable wtWebioEA2x2ERPLoadControlEnable. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an ouput. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0-1: outputs 0-1.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPInputPortTable.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPInputPortTable
wtWebioEA2x2ERPInputPortTable.description: List of settings depending on the input number.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPInputPortEntry.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPInputPortEntry
wtWebioEA2x2ERPInputPortEntry.description: Input parameter for the individual inputs.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortInputMode.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortInputMode
wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortInputMode.description: Binary coded modes: Selecting short pulse detection enable by setting the corresponding bit to 1 enables interrupt support for counting. Only positive edges are accepted as trigger source. The maximum counting frequenz equals 2000 Hz. This mode is available for inputs 0-3 only. Selecting counter clear on read by setting the corresponding bit to 1 enables the corresponding counter to be cleared automatically every time it is read, except HTTP reading with user rights. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. Selection for input 0-1: OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 4-7: unused Bit 3 : Bidirectional counter enable Bit 2 : Counter clear on read Bit 1 : Change detection enable (default) Bit 0 : Short Pulse detection enable

wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortInputFilter.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortInputFilter
wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortInputFilter.description: Pulses with a duration shorter than here specified (duration in 1/1000 sec), are ignored.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortInputBicountPulsePola.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortInputBicountPulsePolarity
wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortInputBicountPulsePola.description: This value defines the polarity of the input pulse. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0 : negative polarity Bit 1 : positive polarity Bit 2-7 : unused

wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortInputBicountInactivTi.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortInputBicountInactivTimeout
wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortInputBicountInactivTi.description: Pulse chains with a duration shorter than here specified (in 1/10 sek), are ignored.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPOutputPortTable.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPOutputPortTable
wtWebioEA2x2ERPOutputPortTable.description: List of settings depending on the output number.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPOutputPortEntry.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPOutputPortEntry
wtWebioEA2x2ERPOutputPortEntry.description: Output parameters of the individual outputs.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortOutputGroupMode.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortOutputGroupMode
wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortOutputGroupMode.description: It is possible to connect outputs together to increase the output current. This could be done by connecting 2 or 4 outputs in a group together. All bits of such a group has to be set all together in the same way. This variable configures this group scheme. If one ouput bit of a group is set, all other output bits of the same group will be set in the same manner. More than one configuration must not be selected. Selection for ouputs 0-1: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0 : ouputs 0,1 disconnected (default) Bit 1 : ouputs 0+1 connected

wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortOutputSafetyState.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortOutputSafetyState
wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortOutputSafetyState.description: This variable allows setting of individual digital outputs. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. The first four OCTETS contain the mask which determines which of the outputs are to be set (corresponding bit = 1) and which outputs are to remain unchanged (corresponding bit = 0): OCTET 1 : unused OCTET 2 : unused OCTET 3 : unused OCTET 4, Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Mask for digital output OCTETS 5-8 contain the level (1=HIGH, 0=LOW) which the outputs to be changed should assume: OCTET 5 : unused OCTET 6 : unused OCTET 7 : unused OCTET 8, Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Level of digital output

wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortLogicInputMask.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortLogicInputMask
wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortLogicInputMask.description: Selecting one of these inputs by setting the corresponding bit to 1 enables the logic function for the output identified by the index within this table. The calculation take place in 4 steps: 1. Selecting inputs (wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortLogicInputMask) 2. Inverting inputs if necessary (wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortLogicInputInverter) 3. Logical combination (wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortLogicFunction) 4. Inverting the result if necessary (wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortLogicOutputInverter) OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0-1 : inputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortLogicInputInverter.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortLogicInputInverter
wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortLogicInputInverter.description: Every input bit selected here will be inverted. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0-1 : inputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortLogicFunction.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortLogicFunction
wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortLogicFunction.description: This determines the logic function. No more than one function may be selected. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0 : logic function OR (default) Bit 1 : logic function AND Bit 2-7 : unused

wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortLogicOutputInverter.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortLogicOutputInverter
wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortLogicOutputInverter.description: The logical operation result could be inverteted by setting the corresponding bit to 1. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0 : Output Inverter enable Bit 1-7 : unused

wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortPulseDuration.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortPulseDuration
wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortPulseDuration.description: Pulse length in 1/1000 sec. Setting this value to zero, disables the pulse output.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortPulsePolarity.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortPulsePolarity
wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortPulsePolarity.description: This value defines the polarity of the output pulse, if wtWebioEA2x2ERPPortPulseDuration is not set to zero. After the pulse is finished, the output switches back to the opposite state. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0 : negative polarity Bit 1 : positive polarity Bit 2-7 : unused

wtWebioEA2x2ERPDiagErrorCount.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPDiagErrorCount
wtWebioEA2x2ERPDiagErrorCount.description: Number of entries in the error memory.

wtWebioEA2x2ERPDiagErrorIndex.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERPDiagErrorIndex
wtWebioEA2x2ERPDiagErrorIndex.description: The value of this variable is used as an index to read an error massege from wtWebioEA2x2ERPDiagErrorMessage. wtWebioEA12x6RelERPInputCounterClear.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPInputCounterClear
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPInputCounterClear.description: Clears the input counter after returning its value.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPInputValue.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPInputValue
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPInputValue.description: This variable is used to read the inputs of the digital I/O port. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3, Bit 0-3: Digital inputs 8-11 Bit 4-7: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-7: Digital inputs 0-7

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputState.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputState
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputState.description: Setting and reading of the states of the outputs.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputValue.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputValue
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputValue.description: This variable is used to read and write the outputs of the digital I/O port. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0-5: Digital outputs 0-5

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSetOutput.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSetOutput
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSetOutput.description: This variable allows setting of individual digital outputs. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. The first two OCTETS contain the mask which determines which of the outputs are to be set (corresponding bit = 1) and which outputs are to remain unchanged (corresponding bit = 0): OCTET 1 : unused OCTET 2 : unused OCTET 3 : unused OCTET 4 : Bit 0-5: Mask for digital outputs 0-5 OCTETS 5-8 contain the level (1=HIGH, 0=LOW) which the inputs should assume: OCTET 5 : unused OCTET 6 : unused OCTET 7 : unused OCTET 8 : Bit 0-5: Level of digital outputs 0-5

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSessCntrlPassword.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSessCntrlPassword
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSessCntrlPassword.description: Entering this password opens a session which is ended by writing a 1 to wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSessCntrlLogout. When read this variable provides a string of length zero.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSessCntrlConfigMode.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSessCntrlConfigMode
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSessCntrlConfigMode.description: When the device is in SNMP configuration mode, the value 1 is returned, otherwise 0. If the read value is 0 even though the password was written, the device is already in config mode and the variables can only be read.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSessCntrlLogout.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSessCntrlLogout
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSessCntrlLogout.description: If the device is in configuration mode and the session was opened by this SNMP Manager, writing a 1 to this variable will end the session and all parameters are stored. Writing a 2 discards all entries again. When read this variable provides the value 0.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSessCntrlAdminPasswor.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSessCntrlAdminPassword
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSessCntrlAdminPasswor.description: This password protects access to the variables with administrator rights. It can only be changed by the administrator. If no password was assigned, the valid password is public.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSessCntrlConfigPasswo.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSessCntrlConfigPassword
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSessCntrlConfigPasswo.description: This password protects access to the variables with configurator rights. It can be changed by the administrator and by the configurator. If no password was assigned, the valid password is public. When read this variable provides a null-pointer.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDeviceName.description: Name of the Webio, which is user definable.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPTzOffsetHrs.description: Offset hours for the time zone (winter time) with respect to UTC.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPTzOffsetMin.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPTzOffsetMin
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPTzOffsetMin.description: Offset minutes for the time zone (winter time) with respect to UTC.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPTzEnable.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPTzEnable
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPTzEnable.description: Binary coded conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Apply Timezone

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzOffsetHrs.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzOffsetHrs
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzOffsetHrs.description: Offset hours of the time zone (summer time) with respect to UTC.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzOffsetMin.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzOffsetMin
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzOffsetMin.description: Offset minutes of the time zone (summer time) with respect to UTC.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzEnable.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzEnable
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzEnable.description: Binary coded conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Apply Summertime

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStartMonth.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStartMonth
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStartMonth.description: Month in which the change is made from winter time to summer time.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStartMode.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStartMode
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStartMode.description: Mode of the day of the week for which the change is made from winter time to summer time.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStartWday.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStartWday
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStartWday.description: Day of the week on which the change is made from winter time to summer time

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStartHrs.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStartHrs
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStartHrs.description: Hour in which the time zone is changed from winter to summer time with respect to UTC.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStartMin.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStartMin
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStartMin.description: Minute in which the time zone is changed from winter to summer time with respect to UTC.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStopMonth.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStopMonth
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStopMonth.description: Month in which the change is made from summer time to winter time.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStopMode.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStopMode
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStopMode.description: Mode of the week day on which the change is made from summer time to winter time.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStopWday.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStopWday
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStopWday.description: Day of the week on which the change is made from summer time to winter time.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStopHrs.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStopHrs
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStopHrs.description: Hour at which the time zone is changed from summer to winter time with respect to UTC.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStopMin.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStopMin
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStTzStopMin.description: Minute at which the time zone is changed from summer to winter time with respect to UTC.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPTimeServer1.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPTimeServer1
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPTimeServer1.description: IP address or name of the 1st time server in ASCII

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPTimeServer2.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPTimeServer2
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPTimeServer2.description: IP address or name of the 2nd time server in ASCII

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPTsEnable.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPTsEnable
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPTsEnable.description: Binary coded conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Apply Time Server

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPTsSyncTime.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPTsSyncTime
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPTsSyncTime.description: Daily synchronisation time with the time server (hour: 0-23).

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPClockHrs.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPClockHrs
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPClockHrs.description: Clock hours taking into account the time zone settings.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPClockMin.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPClockMin
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPClockMin.description: Clock minutes taking into account the time zone settings.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPClockDay.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPClockDay
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPClockDay.description: Date: Day of the month, taking into account the time zone settings.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPClockMonth.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPClockMonth
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPClockMonth.description: Date: Month, taking into account the time zone settings.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPClockYear.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPClockYear
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPClockYear.description: Date: Year, taking into account the time zone settings.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDnsServer1.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDnsServer1
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDnsServer1.description: IP address of the 1st DNS server in ASCII

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDnsServer2.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDnsServer2
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDnsServer2.description: IP address of the 2nd DNS server in ASCII

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAddConfig.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAddConfig
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAddConfig.description: Additional configuration (1=ON): Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1: DHCP enable Bit 0: BOOTP enable

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStartup.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStartup
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPStartup.description: Binary coded start page, more than one page must not be selected: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 2: user.htm Bit 1: home.htm Bit 0: index.htm

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPGetHeaderEnable.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPGetHeaderEnable
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPGetHeaderEnable.description: If bits are set, every answer of a short form GET question will be lead by the IP-address and name of the device (Header) or a HTTP header (HTTP): Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 2-7: unused Bit 1 : GET HTTP enable Bit 0 : GET Header enable

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPHttpInputTrigger.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPHttpInputTrigger
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPHttpInputTrigger.description: Every change on the inputs causes their state to be transmitted to the remote device. To minimize data traffic, individual inputs may be exempted from this rule. Nevertheless every transmission will contain all input bits. If a bit is set (1), a change of state on the corresponding input triggers a transmission. If the bit is not set (0), no transmission takes place. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3, Bit 0-3: Digital inputs 8-11 Bit 4-7: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-7: Digital inputs 0-7

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPHttpPort.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPHttpPort
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPHttpPort.description: Definition of the standard HTML port (Default: 80).

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPMailReply.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPMailReply
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPMailReply.description: Reply address for the mail server.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPMailServer.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPMailServer
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPMailServer.description: Name or IP address of the mail server.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPMailEnable.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPMailEnable
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPMailEnable.description: Set this bit to enable the sending of mails: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Mail enable

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPMailAuthentication.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPMailAuthentication
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPMailAuthentication.description: Selection of the authentication modi: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : POP3 before SMTP Bit 1 : ESMTP, authentication Bit 0 : SMTP, no authentication

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPMailAuthUser.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPMailAuthUser
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPMailAuthUser.description: Name of the user to be authenticated.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPMailPop3Server.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPMailPop3Server
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPMailPop3Server.description: Name or Ip-address of the POP3 Servers.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSnmpEnable.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSnmpEnable
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSnmpEnable.description: Set bit 0 to enable SNMP. If disabled, the device did not respond to any SNMP requests. Bit 1 decided wether the community string of read operations is compared with the system password or not: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : SNMP enable

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSnmpSystemTrapManager.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSnmpSystemTrapManagerIP
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSnmpSystemTrapManager.description: Name or IP address of the TCP server which accepts the system trap.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSnmpSystemTrapEnable.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSnmpSystemTrapEnable
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSnmpSystemTrapEnable.description: Binary coded trigger conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: ColdStart Bit 1: WarmStart Bit 2: Diag messages Bit 3-7: unused

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPUdpAdminPort.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPUdpAdminPort
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPUdpAdminPort.description: Udp port to which the Udp queries ( short form GET requests) can be sent. This port number must be unique within the device.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPUdpEnable.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPUdpEnable
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPUdpEnable.description: Set this bit to enable UDP support: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : UDP enable

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPUdpRemotePort.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPUdpRemotePort
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPUdpRemotePort.description: Udp remote port setting. If this value is set to zero, the source port read from a request will be used as destination port for the answer. A non zero value forced the destination port to this value.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTable.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTable
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTable.description: Table of properties of the binary mode.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryOperationMode.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryOperationMode
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryOperationMode.description: Selection of the operation mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : UDP Peer Bit 1 : TCP Client Bit 0 : TCP Server

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpServerLocalP.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpServerLocalPort
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpServerLocalP.description: Local TCP port for data exchange in this server mode. This port number must be unique within the device. Reserved port number must not be used (refere to the manual).

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpServerInputT.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpServerInputTrigger
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpServerInputT.description: Every change on the inputs causes their state to be transmitted to the remote device. To minimize data traffic, individual inputs may be exempted from this rule. Nevertheless every transmission will contain all input bits. If a bit is set (1), a change of state on the corresponding input triggers a transmission. If the bit is not set (0), no transmission takes place. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3, Bit 0-3: Digital inputs 8-11 Bit 4-7: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-7: Digital inputs 0-7

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpServerApplic.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpServerApplicationMode
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpServerApplic.description: Selection of the application mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 4-7: unused Bit 3 : OPC Device Bit 2 : Box2Box Slave Bit 1 : Compatible 50xxx Bit 0 : Default

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientLocalP.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientLocalPort
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientLocalP.description: Local TCP port for data exchange in this client mode. This port number must be unique within the device. Reserved port number must not be used (refere to the manual).

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientServer.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientServerPort
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientServer.description: Port number of the server. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the server port to zero.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientServer.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientServerIpAddr
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientServer.description: Ip address of the server. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the server IP address to 0.0.0.0.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientServer.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientServerPassword
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientServer.description: Building a connection may be protected by the administrator password of the server. Enter the server password to establish the connection, if a server administrator password exists.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientInacti.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientInactivity
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientInacti.description: Connection timeout in 100ms. If no data are exchanged within the specified time, the device closes the connection to the server. The value 0 deactivates the timer. Using the Box2Box mode this function is disabled.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientInputT.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientInputTrigger
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientInputT.description: Every change on the inputs causes their state to be transmitted to the remote device. To minimize data traffic, individual inputs may be exempted from this rule. Nevertheless every transmission will contain all input bits. If a bit is set (1), a change of state on the corresponding input triggers a transmission. If the bit is not set (0), no transmission takes place. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3, Bit 0-3: Digital inputs 8-11 Bit 4-7: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-7: Digital inputs 0-7

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientInterv.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientInterval
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientInterv.description: Configurable interval with a 100ms base, in which the Webio device sends data to the configured application. A interval of zero stopps the periodical sending.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientApplic.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientApplicationMode
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientApplic.description: Selection of the application mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : Box2Box Slave Bit 1 : Compatible 50xxx Bit 0 : Default

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryUdpPeerLocalPor.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryUdpPeerLocalPort
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryUdpPeerLocalPor.description: Local UDP port for data exchange in this peer to peer mode. This port number must be unique within the device. Reserved port number must not be used (refere to the manual).

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryUdpPeerRemotePo.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryUdpPeerRemotePort
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryUdpPeerRemotePo.description: Port number of the remote device. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the remote port to zero.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryUdpPeerRemoteIp.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryUdpPeerRemoteIpAddr
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryUdpPeerRemoteIp.description: Ip address of the remote device. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the remote device IP address to 0.0.0.0.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryUdpPeerInputTri.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryUdpPeerInputTrigger
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryUdpPeerInputTri.description: Every change on the inputs causes their state to be transmitted to the remote device. To minimize data traffic, individual inputs may be exempted from this rule. Nevertheless every transmission will contain all input bits. If a bit is set (1), a change of state on the corresponding input triggers a transmission. If the bit is not set (0), no transmission takes place. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3, Bit 0-3: Digital inputs 8-11 Bit 4-7: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-7: Digital inputs 0-7

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryUdpPeerInterval.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryUdpPeerInterval
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryUdpPeerInterval.description: Configurable interval with a 100ms base, in which the Webio device sends data to the configured remote device. A interval of zero stopps the periodical sending.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryUdpPeerApplicat.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryUdpPeerApplicationMode
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryUdpPeerApplicat.description: Selection of the application mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : Box2Box Slave Bit 1 : Compatible 50xxx Bit 0 : Default

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryConnectedPort.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryConnectedPort
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryConnectedPort.description: Port number of the remote device, after connection has been established. In case of no connection or missing port informations a zero will be read.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryConnectedIpAddr.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryConnectedIpAddr
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryConnectedIpAddr.description: IP address of the remote device, after connection has been established. In case of no connection or missing port informations 0.0.0.0 will be read.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpServerClient.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpServerClientHttpPort
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpServerClient.description: HTTP port number of the remote device at TCP Server Mode. If an mailfunction occurs status informations will be send to this port. Not used at mode Compatible 50xxx.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientServer.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientServerHttpPort
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPBinaryTcpClientServer.description: HTTP port number of the remote device at TCP Client Mode. In the operating mode Box2Box connection status informations will be exchanged through this port.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSyslogServerIP.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSyslogServerIP
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSyslogServerIP.description: Name or IP address of the Syslog server, which accepts the Syslog messgaes.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSyslogServerPort.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSyslogServerPort
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSyslogServerPort.description: Portnumber of the Syslog servers, default 514.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSyslogSystemMessagesE.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSyslogSystemMessagesEnable
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSyslogSystemMessagesE.description: Binary coded trigger conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: ColdStart Bit 1: WarmStart Bit 2: Diag Messages Bit 3-7: unused

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSyslogEnable.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSyslogEnable
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSyslogEnable.description: Set bit 0to enable Syslog: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Syslog enable

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPFTPServerIP.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPFTPServerIP
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPFTPServerIP.description: Name or IP address of the FTP server, which accepts the FTP messages.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPFTPServerControlPort.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPFTPServerControlPort
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPFTPServerControlPort.description: Portnumber of the control port of the FTP server, default 21.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPFTPOption.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPFTPOption
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPFTPOption.description: Bit 0 switches the FTP Server in Passiv-Mode, the Client controls the data connection on its own: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : PASV enable

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPFTPEnable.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPFTPEnable
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPFTPEnable.description: Set Bit 0 to enable FTP: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : FTP enable

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPWayBackEnable.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPWayBackEnable
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPWayBackEnable.description: Set Bit 0 to enable WayBack: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : WayBack enable

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPWayBackServerControlP.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPWayBackServerControlPort
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPWayBackServerControlP.description: Portnumber of the control port of the FTP server, default 21.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPWayBackFTPPassword.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPWayBackFTPPassword
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPWayBackFTPPassword.description: WayBack FTP Loggin: Password of the user.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPWayBackFTPResponse.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPWayBackFTPResponse
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPWayBackFTPResponse.description: WayBack FTP response: return message after login.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPWayBackFTPTimeOut.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPWayBackFTPTimeOut
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPWayBackFTPTimeOut.description: WayBack FTP Timeout: a request must be finished within this periode of time.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputModeTable.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputModeTable
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputModeTable.description: Table of output mode configurations dependent on the output indices.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputModeEntry.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputModeEntry
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputModeEntry.description: Output mode configurations of the individual outputs.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputModeBit.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputModeBit
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputModeBit.description: This binary coded output mode defines the individual operation mode for any output. More than one mode must not be selected. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each set of octets corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 6-7: unused Bit 5 : Logic Bit 4 : Binary 2 Bit 3 : Binary 1 Bit 2 : SNMP Bit 1 : UDP ASCII Bit 0 : HTTP

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSafetyTimeout.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSafetyTimeout
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPSafetyTimeout.description: After this period of time (multiple of 100ms) without receiving data outputs switch to their Safety States. For each output a independend safety state could be defined.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmTable.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmTable
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmTable.description: List of settings depending on the alarm number.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmEntry.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmEntry
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmEntry.description: Alarm parameters of the individual alarms.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmInputTrigger.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmInputTrigger
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmInputTrigger.description: This variable allows setting of individual input trigger conditions. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. The first four OCTETS contain the mask which determines which of the inputs are to be considered (corresponding bit = 1) and which inputs are to ignore (corresponding bit = 0): OCTET 1 : unused OCTET 2 : unused OCTET 3, Bit 0-3: Mask for digital inputs 8-11 Bit 4-7: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-7: Mask for digital inputs 0-7 OCTETS 5-8 contain the level (1=HIGH, 0=LOW) which the inputs should assume: OCTET 5 : unused OCTET 6 : unused OCTET 7, Bit 0-3: Level of digital inputs 8-11 Bit 4-7: unused OCTET 8, Bit 0-7: Level of digital inputs 0-7 OCTETS 9-12 contain the ANY bit (1=ON, 0=OFF). Inputs masked with the any bit trigger with any change of the corresponding input bit. Settings in OCTET 5-9 are then unused: OCTET 9 : unused OCTET 11, Bit 0-7 : ANY bits of digital inputs 8-11 Bit 12-15 : unused OCTET 12, Bit 0-7 : ANY bits of digital inputs 0-7

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmOutputTrigger.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmOutputTrigger
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmOutputTrigger.description: This variable allows setting of individual output trigger conditions. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. The first four OCTETS contain the mask which determines which of the outputs are to be considered (corresponding bit = 1) and which outputs are to ignore (corresponding bit = 0): OCTET 1 : unused OCTET 2 : unused OCTET 3 : unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-5: Mask for digital outputs 0-5 OCTETS 5-8 contain the level (1=HIGH, 0=LOW) which the outputs should assume: OCTET 5 : unused OCTET 6 : unused OCTET 7 : unused OCTET 8, Bit 0-5: Level of digital outputs 0-5 OCTETS 9-12 contain the ANY bit (1=ON, 0=OFF). Outputs masked with the any bit trigger with any change of the corresponding output bit. Settings in OCTET 5-9 are then unused: OCTET 9 : unused OCTET 10: unused OCTET 11: unused OCTET 12: Bit 0-5: ANY bits of digital outputs 0-5

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSystemTrigger.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSystemTrigger
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSystemTrigger.description: Binary coded trigger conditions: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 4-7: unused Bit 3 : Warm Start Bit 2 : Cold Start Bit 1 : Timer Bit 0 : Load Control

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmMaxCounterValue.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmMaxCounterValue
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmMaxCounterValue.description: This variable configures a max. counter value. If an input counter value exceeds this max. value, the corresponding alarm is triggered. Input counters with its mask bit unset in wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmInputTrigger are not considered.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmEnable.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmEnable
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmEnable.description: Binary coded alarm enable: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: Mail Enable Bit 1: SNMP Trap enable Bit 2: UDP enable Bit 3: Send inputs to pending TCP connections Bit 4: TCP Client enable Bit 5: Syslog Messages enable Bit 6-7: unused

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmMailAddr.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmMailAddr
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmMailAddr.description: E-Mail address for sending the alarm mail to.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmMailText.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmMailText
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmMailText.description: Alarm mail text: States of the Webio device can be included by using special tags. Please refer to the respective Webio manual

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSnmpManagerIP.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSnmpManagerIP
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSnmpManagerIP.description: IP address of the SNMP Manager to which the Webio device should send SNMP traps.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSnmpTrapText.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSnmpTrapText
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSnmpTrapText.description: This text appears in the trap body.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmUdpIpAddr.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmUdpIpAddr
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmUdpIpAddr.description: IP address of the UDP listener to which the Webio device should send UDP traps.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmUdpPort.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmUdpPort
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmUdpPort.description: Port number of the UDP listener to which the Webio device should send UDP traps.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmUdpText.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmUdpText
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmUdpText.description: This text appears in the UDP trap body.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmTcpIpAddr.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmTcpIpAddr
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmTcpIpAddr.description: IP address of the TCP listener to which the Webio device should send TCP traps.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmTcpPort.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmTcpPort
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmTcpPort.description: Port number of the TCP listener to which the Webio device should send TCP traps.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmTcpText.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmTcpText
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmTcpText.description: This text appears in the TCP trap body.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSyslogIpAddr.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSyslogIpAddr
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSyslogIpAddr.description: IP address of the syslog server to which the Webio device should send syslog messages.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSyslogPort.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSyslogPort
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSyslogPort.description: Port number of the syslog server to which the Webio device should send syslog messages.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSyslogText.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSyslogText
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSyslogText.description: Every message starts with the priority key, a time stamp and the host ip address, according RFC3164. This text appears in the following syslog message body.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmFtpDataPort.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmFtpDataPort
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmFtpDataPort.description: Local data port: 1..65535 or AUTO: the next free port will be assigned.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmFtpFileName.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmFtpFileName
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmFtpFileName.description: Name of the file including path informations.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmFtpText.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmFtpText
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmFtpText.description: Message text to store on the FTP server.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmFtpOption.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmFtpOption
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmFtpOption.description: Binary coded options, select only one option at the same time: STORE = replace file APPEND = append message at the end of the file Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0 : STORE Bit 1 : APPEND Bit 2-7: unused

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmTimerCron.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmTimerCron
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmTimerCron.description: This entry contains 5 space or tab seperated text fields for time trigger definition. Each field must match with the actual time to trigger a message, weekday and day of month are interpreted separatley. 1: Minutes Range 0-59 2. Hours Range 0-23, 0 is midnight 3: Day of month Range 1-31 4: Month Range 1-12 5: Weekday Range 0-6, 0 is sunday Syntax for every field: - an asterix (*) enables every possible setting of a field - single numbers seperated by commas - a partition within the allowed range (1-5) - step size within an partition of the allowed range (0-59/2: every second minute).

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmMailReleaseText.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmMailReleaseText
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmMailReleaseText.description: Release Alarm mail text: States of the Webio device can be included by using special tags. Please refer to the respective Webio manual

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSnmpTrapReleaseT.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSnmpTrapReleaseText
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSnmpTrapReleaseT.description: This text appears in the trap body.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmUdpReleaseText.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmUdpReleaseText
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmUdpReleaseText.description: This text appears in the UDP trap body.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmTcpReleaseText.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmTcpReleaseText
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmTcpReleaseText.description: This text appears in the TCP trap body.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSyslogReleaseTex.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSyslogReleaseText
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmSyslogReleaseTex.description: Every message starts with the priority key, a time stamp and the host ip address, according RFC3164. This text appears in the following syslog message body.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmFtpReleaseText.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmFtpReleaseText
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlarmFtpReleaseText.description: Message text to store on the FTP server.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPInputPortTable.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPInputPortTable
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPInputPortTable.description: List of settings depending on the input number.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPInputPortEntry.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPInputPortEntry
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPInputPortEntry.description: Input parameter for the individual inputs.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortInputMode.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortInputMode
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortInputMode.description: Binary coded modes: Selecting short pulse detection enable by setting the corresponding bit to 1 enables interrupt support for counting. Only positive edges are accepted as trigger source. The maximum counting frequenz equals 2000 Hz. This mode is available for inputs 0-3 only. Selecting counter clear on read by setting the corresponding bit to 1 enables the corresponding counter to be cleared automatically every time it is read, except HTTP reading with user rights. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. Selection for input 0-3: OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : Counter clear on read Bit 1 : Change detection enable (default) Bit 0 : Short Pulse detection enable Selection for inputs 4-11: OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 2-7: unused Bit 1 : Counter clear on read Bit 0 : Change detection enable (default)

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortInputFilter.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortInputFilter
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortInputFilter.description: Pulses with a duration shorter than here specified (duration in 1/1000 sec), are ignored.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortInputBicountPulse.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortInputBicountPulsePolarity
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortInputBicountPulse.description: This value defines the polarity of the input pulse. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0 : negative polarity Bit 1 : positive polarity Bit 2-7 : unused

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortInputBicountInact.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortInputBicountInactivTimeout
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortInputBicountInact.description: Pulse chains with a duration shorter than here specified (in 1/10 sek), are ignored.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputPortTable.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputPortTable
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputPortTable.description: List of settings depending on the output number.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputPortEntry.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputPortEntry
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPOutputPortEntry.description: Output parameters of the individual outputs.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortOutputSafetyState.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortOutputSafetyState
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortOutputSafetyState.description: This variable allows setting of individual digital outputs. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. The first four OCTETS contain the mask which determines which of the outputs are to be set (corresponding bit = 1) and which outputs are to remain unchanged (corresponding bit = 0): OCTET 1 : unused OCTET 2 : unused OCTET 3 : unused OCTET 4, Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Mask for digital output OCTETS 5-8 contain the level (1=HIGH=Relais closed, 0=LOW Relais open) which the outputs to be changed should assume: OCTET 5 : unused OCTET 6 : unused OCTET 7 : unused OCTET 8, Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Level of digital output

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortLogicInputMask.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortLogicInputMask
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortLogicInputMask.description: Selecting one of these inputs by setting the corresponding bit to 1 enables the logic function for the output identified by the index within this table. The calculation take place in 4 steps: 1. Selecting inputs (wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortLogicInputMask) 2. Inverting inputs if necessary (wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortLogicInputInverter) 3. Logical combination (wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortLogicFunction) 4. Inverting the result if necessary (wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortLogicOutputInverter) OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: Bit 0-3 : inputs 8-11 Bit 4-7 : unused OCTET 4: Bit 0-7 : inputs 0-7

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortLogicInputInverte.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortLogicInputInverter
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortLogicInputInverte.description: Every input bit selected here will be inverted. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: Bit 0-3 : inputs 8-11 Bit 4-7 : unused OCTET 4: Bit 0-7 : inputs 0-7

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortLogicFunction.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortLogicFunction
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortLogicFunction.description: This determines the logic function. No more than one function may be selected. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0 : logic function OR (default) Bit 1 : logic function AND Bit 2-7 : unused

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortLogicOutputInvert.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortLogicOutputInverter
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortLogicOutputInvert.description: The logical operation result could be inverteted by setting the corresponding bit to 1. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0 : Output Inverter enable Bit 1-7 : unused

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortPulseDuration.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortPulseDuration
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortPulseDuration.description: Pulse length in 1/1000 sec. Setting this value to zero, disables the pulse output.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortPulsePolarity.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortPulsePolarity
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortPulsePolarity.description: This value defines the polarity of the output pulse, if wtWebioEA12x6RelERPPortPulseDuration is not set to zero. After the pulse is finished, the output switches back to the opposite state. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0 : negative polarity Bit 1 : positive polarity Bit 2-7 : unused

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDiagErrorCount.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDiagErrorCount
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDiagErrorCount.description: Number of entries in the error memory.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDiagErrorIndex.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDiagErrorIndex
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDiagErrorIndex.description: The value of this variable is used as an index to read an error massege from wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDiagErrorMessage. Errors are numbered from 1 to wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDiagErrorCount. Writing a valid value into this variable, making the appropriate message readable from wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDiagErrorMessage.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDiagErrorMessage.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDiagErrorMessage
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDiagErrorMessage.description: Using wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDiagErrorIndex as an index, the appropriate message is available.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDiagErrorClear.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDiagErrorClear
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPDiagErrorClear.description: Writing 1 into this variable clears all diagnosis messages.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlert1.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlert1
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlert1.description: This SNMP trap is generated when Alarm 1 was triggered, SNMP trap enable is set and SNMP is enabled.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlert2.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlert2
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlert2.description: This SNMP trap is generated when Alarm 2 was triggered, SNMP trap enable is set and SNMP is enabled.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlert3.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlert3
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlert3.description: This SNMP trap is generated when Alarm 3 was triggered, SNMP trap enable is set and SNMP is enabled.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlert4.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlert4
wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlert4.description: This SNMP trap is generated when Alarm 4 was triggered, SNMP trap enable is set and SNMP is enabled.

wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlert5.name: wtWebioEA12x6RelERPAlert5

wtIpWatcherInputCounterClear.name: wtIpWatcherInputCounterClear
wtIpWatcherInputCounterClear.description: Clears the input counter after returning its value.

wtIpWatcherInputState.name: wtIpWatcherInputState
wtIpWatcherInputState.description: Value of a single input bit.

wtIpWatcherInputValue.name: wtIpWatcherInputValue
wtIpWatcherInputValue.description: This variable is used to read the inputs of the digital I/O port. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Digital outputs 0-1

wtIpWatcherOutputState.name: wtIpWatcherOutputState
wtIpWatcherOutputState.description: Value of a single output bit.

wtIpWatcherOutputValue.name: wtIpWatcherOutputValue
wtIpWatcherOutputValue.description: This variable is used to read and write the outputs of the digital I/O port. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Digital outputs 0-1 Bit 2-7: ungenutzt

wtIpWatcherSetOutput.name: wtIpWatcherSetOutput
wtIpWatcherSetOutput.description: This variable allows setting of individual digital outputs. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. The first two OCTETS contain the mask which determines which of the outputs are to be set (corresponding bit = 1) and which outputs are to remain unchanged (corresponding bit = 0): OCTET 1 : unused OCTET 2 : unused OCTET 3 : unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Mask for digital outputs 0-1 OCTETS 5-8 contain the level (1=HIGH, 0=LOW) which the outputs should assume: OCTET 5 : unused OCTET 6 : unused OCTET 7 : unused OCTET 8, Bit 0-1: Level of digital outputs 0-1

wtIpWatcherSessCntrlPassword.name: wtIpWatcherSessCntrlPassword
wtIpWatcherSessCntrlPassword.description: Entering this password opens a session which is ended by writing a 1 to wtIpWatcherSessCntrlLogout. When read this variable provides a string of length zero.

wtIpWatcherSessCntrlConfigMode.name: wtIpWatcherSessCntrlConfigMode
wtIpWatcherSessCntrlConfigMode.description: When the device is in SNMP configuration mode, the value 1 is returned, otherwise 0. If the read value is 0 even though the password was written, the device is already in config mode and the variables can only be read.

wtIpWatcherSessCntrlLogout.name: wtIpWatcherSessCntrlLogout
wtIpWatcherSessCntrlLogout.description: If the device is in configuration mode and the session was opened by this SNMP Manager, writing a 1 to this variable will end the session and all parameters are stored. Writing a 2 discards all entries again. When read this variable provides the value 0.

wtIpWatcherSessCntrlAdminPassword.name: wtIpWatcherSessCntrlAdminPassword
wtIpWatcherSessCntrlAdminPassword.description: This password protects access to the variables with administrator rights. It can only be changed by the administrator. If no password was assigned, the valid password is public.

wtIpWatcherSessCntrlConfigPassword.name: wtIpWatcherSessCntrlConfigPassword
wtIpWatcherSessCntrlConfigPassword.description: This password protects access to the variables with configurator rights. It can be changed by the administrator and by the configurator. If no password was assigned, the valid password is public. When read this variable provides a null-pointer.

wtIpWatcherTzEnable.description: Binary coded conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Apply Timezone

wtIpWatcherStTzOffsetMin.name: wtIpWatcherStTzOffsetMin
wtIpWatcherStTzOffsetMin.description: Offset minutes of the time zone (summer time) with respect to UTC.

wtIpWatcherStTzStopWday.name: wtIpWatcherStTzStopWday

wtIpWatcherStTzStopHrs.name: wtIpWatcherStTzStopHrs

wtIpWatcherStTzStopMin.name: wtIpWatcherStTzStopMin
wtIpWatcherStTzStopMin.description: Minute at which the time zone is changed from summer to winter time with respect to UTC.

wtIpWatcherMailAuthentication.description: Selection of the authentication modi: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : POP3 before SMTP Bit 1 : ESMTP, authentication Bit 0 : SMTP, no authentication

wtIpWatcherMailPop3Server.description: Name or Ip-address of the POP3 Servers.

wtIpWatcherSnmpEnable.description: Set bit 0 to enable SNMP. If disabled, the device did not respond to any SNMP requests. Bit 1 decided wether the community string of read operations is compared with the system password or not: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : SNMP enable

wtIpWatcherIpListEnable.description: Binary coded alarm enable: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: enabled in Alarm 1 Bit 1: enabled in Alarm 2 Bit 2: enabled in Alarm 3 Bit 3: enabled in Alarm 4 Bit 4-7: unused

wtIpWatcherAlarmMailAddr.description: E-Mail address for sending the alarm mail to.

wtIpWatcherAlarmSyslogText.description: Every message starts with the priority key, a time stamp and the host ip address, according RFC3164. This text appears in the following syslog message body.

wtIpWatcherAlarmTimerCron.name: wtIpWatcherAlarmTimerCron
wtIpWatcherAlarmTimerCron.description: This entry contains 5 space or tab seperated text fields for time trigger definition. Each field must match with the actual time to trigger a message, weekday and day of month are interpreted separatley. 1: Minutes Range 0-59 2. Hours Range 0-23, 0 is midnight 3: Day of month Range 1-31 4: Month Range 1-12 5: Weekday Range 0-6, 0 is sunday Syntax for every field: - an asterix (*) enables every possible setting of a field - single numbers seperated by commas - a partition within the allowed range (1-5) - step size within an partition of the allowed range (0-59/2: every second minute).

wtWebioEA2x2_24VInputState.description: Value of a single input bit.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VInputValue.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VInputValue
wtWebioEA2x2_24VInputValue.description: This variable is used to read the inputs of the digital I/O port. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Digital outputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputState.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputState
wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputState.description: Value of a single output bit.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputValue.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputValue
wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputValue.description: This variable is used to read and write the outputs of the digital I/O port. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Digital outputs 0-1 Bit 2-7: ungenutzt

wtWebioEA2x2_24VSetOutput.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VSetOutput
wtWebioEA2x2_24VSetOutput.description: This variable allows setting of individual digital outputs. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. The first two OCTETS contain the mask which determines which of the outputs are to be set (corresponding bit = 1) and which outputs are to remain unchanged (corresponding bit = 0): OCTET 1 : unused OCTET 2 : unused OCTET 3 : unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Mask for digital outputs 0-1 OCTETS 5-8 contain the level (1=HIGH, 0=LOW) which the outputs should assume: OCTET 5 : unused OCTET 6 : unused OCTET 7 : unused OCTET 8, Bit 0-1: Level of digital outputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2_24VSessCntrlPassword.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VSessCntrlPassword
wtWebioEA2x2_24VSessCntrlPassword.description: Entering this password opens a session which is ended by writing a 1 to wtWebioEA2x2_24VSessCntrlLogout. When read this variable provides a string of length zero.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VSessCntrlConfigMode.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VSessCntrlConfigMode
wtWebioEA2x2_24VSessCntrlConfigMode.description: When the device is in SNMP configuration mode, the value 1 is returned, otherwise 0. If the read value is 0 even though the password was written, the device is already in config mode and the variables can only be read.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VSessCntrlLogout.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VSessCntrlLogout
wtWebioEA2x2_24VSessCntrlLogout.description: If the device is in configuration mode and the session was opened by this SNMP Manager, writing a 1 to this variable will end the session and all parameters are stored. Writing a 2 discards all entries again. When read this variable provides the value 0.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VSessCntrlAdminPassword.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VSessCntrlAdminPassword
wtWebioEA2x2_24VSessCntrlAdminPassword.description: This password protects access to the variables with administrator rights. It can only be changed by the administrator. If no password was assigned, the valid password is public.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VSessCntrlConfigPassword.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VSessCntrlConfigPassword
wtWebioEA2x2_24VSessCntrlConfigPassword.description: This password protects access to the variables with configurator rights. It can be changed by the administrator and by the configurator. If no password was assigned, the valid password is public. When read this variable provides a null-pointer.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VStartup.description: Binary coded start page, more than one page must not be selected: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 2: user.htm Bit 1: home.htm Bit 0: index.htm

wtWebioEA2x2_24VGetHeaderEnable.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VGetHeaderEnable
wtWebioEA2x2_24VGetHeaderEnable.description: If bits are set, every answer of a short form GET question will be lead by the IP-address and name of the device (Header) or a HTTP header (HTTP): Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 2-7: unused Bit 1 : GET HTTP enable Bit 0 : GET Header enable

wtWebioEA2x2_24VHttpInputTrigger.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VHttpInputTrigger
wtWebioEA2x2_24VHttpInputTrigger.description: Every change on the inputs causes their state to be transmitted to the remote device. To minimize data traffic, individual inputs may be exempted from this rule. Nevertheless every transmission will contain all input bits. If a bit is set (1), a change of state on the corresponding input triggers a transmission. If the bit is not set (0), no transmission takes place. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Digital inputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2_24VMailAuthentication.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VMailAuthentication
wtWebioEA2x2_24VMailAuthentication.description: Selection of the authentication modi: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : POP3 before SMTP Bit 1 : ESMTP, authentication Bit 0 : SMTP, no authentication

wtWebioEA2x2_24VMailAuthUser.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VMailAuthUser
