wtWebioEA2x2_24VSnmpEnable.description: Set bit 0 to enable SNMP. If disabled, the device did not respond to any SNMP requests. Bit 1 decided wether the community string of read operations is compared with the system password or not: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : SNMP enable

wtWebioEA2x2_24VUdpEnable.description: Set this bit to enable UDP support: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : UDP enable

wtWebioEA2x2_24VUdpRemotePort.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VUdpRemotePort
wtWebioEA2x2_24VUdpRemotePort.description: Udp remote port setting. If this value is set to zero, the source port read from a request will be used as destination port for the answer. A non zero value forced the destination port to this value.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTable.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTable
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTable.description: Table of properties of the binary mode.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryOperationMode.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryOperationMode
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryOperationMode.description: Selection of the operation mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : UDP Peer Bit 1 : TCP Client Bit 0 : TCP Server

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpServerLocalPort.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpServerLocalPort
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpServerLocalPort.description: Local TCP port for data exchange in this server mode. This port number must be unique within the device. Reserved port number must not be used (refere to the manual).

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpServerInputTrig.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpServerInputTrigger
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpServerInputTrig.description: Every change on the inputs causes their state to be transmitted to the remote device. To minimize data traffic, individual inputs may be exempted from this rule. Nevertheless every transmission will contain all input bits. If a bit is set (1), a change of state on the corresponding input triggers a transmission. If the bit is not set (0), no transmission takes place. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Digital inputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpServerApplicati.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpServerApplicationMode
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpServerApplicati.description: Selection of the application mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 4-7: unused Bit 3 : OPC Device Bit 2 : Box2Box Slave Bit 1 : Compatible 50xxx Bit 0 : Default

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientLocalPort.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientLocalPort
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientLocalPort.description: Local TCP port for data exchange in this client mode. This port number must be unique within the device. Reserved port number must not be used (refere to the manual).

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientServerPor.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientServerPort
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientServerPor.description: Port number of the server. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the server port to zero.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientServerIpA.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientServerIpAddr
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientServerIpA.description: Ip address of the server. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the server IP address to 0.0.0.0.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientServerPas.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientServerPassword
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientServerPas.description: Building a connection may be protected by the administrator password of the server. Enter the server password to establish the connection, if a server administrator password exists.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientInactivit.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientInactivity
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientInactivit.description: Connection timeout in 100ms. If no data are exchanged within the specified time, the device closes the connection to the server. The value 0 deactivates the timer. Using the Box2Box mode this function is disabled.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientInputTrig.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientInputTrigger
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientInputTrig.description: Every change on the inputs causes their state to be transmitted to the remote device. To minimize data traffic, individual inputs may be exempted from this rule. Nevertheless every transmission will contain all input bits. If a bit is set (1), a change of state on the corresponding input triggers a transmission. If the bit is not set (0), no transmission takes place. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Digital inputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientInterval.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientInterval
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientInterval.description: Configurable interval with a 100ms base, in which the Webio device sends data to the configured application. A interval of zero stopps the periodical sending.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientApplicati.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientApplicationMode
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientApplicati.description: Selection of the application mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : Box2Box Slave Bit 1 : Compatible 50xxx Bit 0 : Default

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryUdpPeerLocalPort.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryUdpPeerLocalPort
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryUdpPeerLocalPort.description: Local UDP port for data exchange in this peer to peer mode. This port number must be unique within the device. Reserved port number must not be used (refere to the manual).

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryUdpPeerRemotePort.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryUdpPeerRemotePort
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryUdpPeerRemotePort.description: Port number of the remote device. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the remote port to zero.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryUdpPeerRemoteIpAdd.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryUdpPeerRemoteIpAddr
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryUdpPeerRemoteIpAdd.description: Ip address of the remote device. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the remote device IP address to 0.0.0.0.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryUdpPeerInputTrigge.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryUdpPeerInputTrigger
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryUdpPeerInputTrigge.description: Every change on the inputs causes their state to be transmitted to the remote device. To minimize data traffic, individual inputs may be exempted from this rule. Nevertheless every transmission will contain all input bits. If a bit is set (1), a change of state on the corresponding input triggers a transmission. If the bit is not set (0), no transmission takes place. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Digital inputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryUdpPeerInterval.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryUdpPeerInterval
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryUdpPeerInterval.description: Configurable interval with a 100ms base, in which the Webio device sends data to the configured remote device. A interval of zero stopps the periodical sending.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryUdpPeerApplication.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryUdpPeerApplicationMode
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryUdpPeerApplication.description: Selection of the application mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : Box2Box Slave Bit 1 : Compatible 50xxx Bit 0 : Default

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryConnectedPort.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryConnectedPort
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryConnectedPort.description: Port number of the remote device, after connection has been established. In case of no connection or missing port informations a zero will be read.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryConnectedIpAddr.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryConnectedIpAddr
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryConnectedIpAddr.description: IP address of the remote device, after connection has been established. In case of no connection or missing port informations 0.0.0.0 will be read.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpServerClientHtt.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpServerClientHttpPort
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpServerClientHtt.description: HTTP port number of the remote device at TCP Server Mode. If an mailfunction occurs status informations will be send to this port. Not used at mode Compatible 50xxx.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientServerHtt.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientServerHttpPort
wtWebioEA2x2_24VBinaryTcpClientServerHtt.description: HTTP port number of the remote device at TCP Client Mode. In the operating mode Box2Box connection status informations will be exchanged through this port.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VSyslogServerIP.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VSyslogServerIP
wtWebioEA2x2_24VSyslogServerIP.description: Name or IP address of the Syslog server, which accepts the Syslog messgaes.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VSyslogServerPort.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VSyslogServerPort
wtWebioEA2x2_24VSyslogServerPort.description: Portnumber of the Syslog servers, default 514.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VSyslogSystemMessagesEnab.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VSyslogSystemMessagesEnable
wtWebioEA2x2_24VSyslogSystemMessagesEnab.description: Binary coded trigger conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: ColdStart Bit 1: WarmStart Bit 2: Diag Messages Bit 3-7: unused

wtWebioEA2x2_24VSyslogEnable.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VSyslogEnable
wtWebioEA2x2_24VSyslogEnable.description: Set bit 0to enable Syslog: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Syslog enable

wtWebioEA2x2_24VFTPServerIP.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VFTPServerIP
wtWebioEA2x2_24VFTPServerIP.description: Name or IP address of the FTP server, which accepts the FTP messages.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VFTPServerControlPort.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VFTPServerControlPort
wtWebioEA2x2_24VFTPServerControlPort.description: Portnumber of the control port of the FTP server, default 21.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VFTPOption.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VFTPOption
wtWebioEA2x2_24VFTPOption.description: Bit 0 switches the FTP Server in Passiv-Mode, the Client controls the data connection on its own: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : PASV enable

wtWebioEA2x2_24VFTPEnable.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VFTPEnable
wtWebioEA2x2_24VFTPEnable.description: Set Bit 0 to enable FTP: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : FTP enable

wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputModeTable.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputModeTable
wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputModeTable.description: Table of output mode configurations dependent on the output indices.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputModeEntry.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputModeEntry
wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputModeEntry.description: Output mode configurations of the individual outputs.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputModeBit.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputModeBit
wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputModeBit.description: This binary coded output mode defines the individual operation mode for any output. More than one mode must not be selected. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 6-7: unused Bit 5 : Logic Bit 4 : Binary 2 Bit 3 : Binary 1 Bit 2 : SNMP Bit 1 : UDP ASCII Bit 0 : HTTP

wtWebioEA2x2_24VSafetyTimeout.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VSafetyTimeout
wtWebioEA2x2_24VSafetyTimeout.description: After this period of time (multiple of 100ms) without receiving data outputs switch to their Safety States. For each output a independend safety state could be defined.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VPowerSupplyEnable.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VPowerSupplyEnable
wtWebioEA2x2_24VPowerSupplyEnable.description: Setting this enable bit turns on the intarnal 24V power supply of the outputs. All currents out must not exceed 150mA. At overcurrent condition the power supply will be shut down automatically. To reset the ocvercurrent protection circuit write 1 into wtWebioEA2x2_24VDiagErrorClear. Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Power Supply enable

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmTable.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmTable
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmTable.description: List of settings depending on the alarm number.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmEntry.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmEntry
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmEntry.description: Alarm parameters of the individual alarms.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmInputTrigger.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmInputTrigger
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmInputTrigger.description: This variable allows setting of individual input trigger conditions. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. The first four OCTETS contain the mask which determines which of the inputs are to be considered (corresponding bit = 1) and which inputs are to ignore (corresponding bit = 0): OCTET 1 : unused OCTET 2 : unused OCTET 3 : unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Mask for digital inputs 0-1 OCTETS 5-8 contain the level (1=HIGH, 0=LOW) which the inputs should assume: OCTET 5 : unused OCTET 6 : unused OCTET 7 : unused OCTET 8, Bit 0-1: Level of digital inputs 0-1 OCTETS 9-12 contain the ANY bit (1=ON, 0=OFF). Inputs masked with the any bit trigger with any change of the corresponding input bit. Settings in OCTET 5-9 are then unused: OCTET 9: unused OCTET 10: unused OCTET 11: unused OCTET 12, Bit 0-1: ANY bits of digital inputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmOutputTrigger.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmOutputTrigger
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmOutputTrigger.description: This variable allows setting of individual output trigger conditions. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. The first four OCTETS contain the mask which determines which of the outputs are to be considered (corresponding bit = 1) and which outputs are to ignore (corresponding bit = 0): OCTET 1 : unused OCTET 2 : unused OCTET 3 : unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Mask for digital outputs 0-1 OCTETS 5-8 contain the level (1=HIGH, 0=LOW) which the outputs should assume: OCTET 5 : unused OCTET 6 : unused OCTET 7 : unused OCTET 8, Bit 0-1: Level of digital outputs 0-1 OCTETS 9-12 contain the ANY bit (1=ON, 0=OFF). Outputs masked with the any bit trigger with any change of the corresponding output bit. Settings in OCTET 5-9 are then unused: OCTET 9: unused OCTET 10: unused OCTET 11: unused OCTET 12, Bit 0-1: ANY bits of digital outputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSystemTrigger.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSystemTrigger
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSystemTrigger.description: Binary coded trigger conditions: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 4-7: unused Bit 3 : Warm Start Bit 2 : Cold Start Bit 1 : Timer Bit 0 : unused

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmMaxCounterValue.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmMaxCounterValue
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmMaxCounterValue.description: This variable configures a max. counter value. If an input counter value exceeds this max. value, the corresponding alarm is triggered. Input counters with its mask bit unset in wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmInputTrigger are not considered.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmEnable.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmEnable
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmEnable.description: Binary coded alarm enable: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: Mail Enable Bit 1: SNMP Trap enable Bit 2: UDP enable Bit 3: Send inputs to pending TCP connections Bit 4: TCP Client enable Bit 5: Syslog Messages enable Bit 6-7: unused

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmMailAddr.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmMailAddr
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmMailAddr.description: E-Mail address for sending the alarm mail to.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmMailText.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmMailText
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmMailText.description: Alarm mail text: States of the Webio device can be included by using special tags. Please refer to the respective Webio manual

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSnmpManagerIP.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSnmpManagerIP
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSnmpManagerIP.description: IP address of the SNMP Manager to which the Webio device should send SNMP traps.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSnmpTrapText.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSnmpTrapText
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSnmpTrapText.description: This text appears in the trap body.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmUdpIpAddr.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmUdpIpAddr
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmUdpIpAddr.description: IP address of the UDP listener to which the Webio device should send UDP traps.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmUdpPort.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmUdpPort
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmUdpPort.description: Port number of the UDP listener to which the Webio device should send UDP traps.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmUdpText.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmUdpText
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmUdpText.description: This text appears in the UDP trap body.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmTcpIpAddr.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmTcpIpAddr
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmTcpIpAddr.description: IP address of the TCP listener to which the Webio device should send TCP traps.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmTcpPort.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmTcpPort
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmTcpPort.description: Port number of the TCP listener to which the Webio device should send TCP traps.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmTcpText.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmTcpText
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmTcpText.description: This text appears in the TCP trap body.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSyslogIpAddr.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSyslogIpAddr
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSyslogIpAddr.description: IP address of the syslog server to which the Webio device should send syslog messages.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSyslogPort.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSyslogPort
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSyslogPort.description: Port number of the syslog server to which the Webio device should send syslog messages.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSyslogText.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSyslogText
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSyslogText.description: Every message starts with the priority key, a time stamp and the host ip address, according RFC3164. This text appears in the following syslog message body.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmFtpDataPort.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmFtpDataPort
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmFtpDataPort.description: Local data port: 1..65535 or AUTO: the next free port will be assigned.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmFtpFileName.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmFtpFileName
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmFtpFileName.description: Name of the file including path informations.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmFtpText.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmFtpText
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmFtpText.description: Message text to store on the FTP server.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmFtpOption.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmFtpOption
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmFtpOption.description: Binary coded options, select only one option at the same time: STORE = replace file APPEND = append message at the end of the file Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0 : STORE Bit 1 : APPEND Bit 2-7: unused

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmTimerCron.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmTimerCron
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmTimerCron.description: This entry contains 5 space or tab seperated text fields for time trigger definition. Each field must match with the actual time to trigger a message, weekday and day of month are interpreted separatley. 1: Minutes Range 0-59 2. Hours Range 0-23, 0 is midnight 3: Day of month Range 1-31 4: Month Range 1-12 5: Weekday Range 0-6, 0 is sunday Syntax for every field: - an asterix (*) enables every possible setting of a field - single numbers seperated by commas - a partition within the allowed range (1-5) - step size within an partition of the allowed range (0-59/2: every second minute).

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmMailReleaseText.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmMailReleaseText
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmMailReleaseText.description: Release Alarm mail text: States of the Webio device can be included by using special tags. Please refer to the respective Webio manual

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSnmpTrapReleaseText.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSnmpTrapReleaseText
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSnmpTrapReleaseText.description: This text appears in the trap body.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmUdpReleaseText.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmUdpReleaseText
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmUdpReleaseText.description: This text appears in the UDP trap body.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmTcpReleaseText.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmTcpReleaseText
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmTcpReleaseText.description: This text appears in the TCP trap body.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSyslogReleaseText.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSyslogReleaseText
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmSyslogReleaseText.description: Every message starts with the priority key, a time stamp and the host ip address, according RFC3164. This text appears in the following syslog message body.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmFtpReleaseText.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmFtpReleaseText
wtWebioEA2x2_24VAlarmFtpReleaseText.description: Message text to store on the FTP server.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VInputPortTable.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VInputPortTable
wtWebioEA2x2_24VInputPortTable.description: List of settings depending on the input number.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VInputPortEntry.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VInputPortEntry
wtWebioEA2x2_24VInputPortEntry.description: Input parameter for the individual inputs.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortInputMode.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortInputMode
wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortInputMode.description: Binary coded modes: Selecting short pulse detection enable by setting the corresponding bit to 1 enables interrupt support for counting. Only positive edges are accepted as trigger source. The maximum counting frequenz equals 2000 Hz. This mode is available for inputs 0-3 only. Selecting counter clear on read by setting the corresponding bit to 1 enables the corresponding counter to be cleared automatically every time it is read, except HTTP reading with user rights. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. Selection for input 0-1: OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 4-7: unused Bit 3 : Bidirectional counter enable Bit 2 : Counter clear on read Bit 1 : Change detection enable (default) Bit 0 : Short Pulse detection enable

wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortInputFilter.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortInputFilter
wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortInputFilter.description: Pulses with a duration shorter than here specified (duration in 1/1000 sec), are ignored.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortInputBicountPulsePol.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortInputBicountPulsePolarity
wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortInputBicountPulsePol.description: This value defines the polarity of the input pulse. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0 : negative polarity Bit 1 : positive polarity Bit 2-7 : unused

wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortInputBicountInactivT.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortInputBicountInactivTimeout
wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortInputBicountInactivT.description: Pulse chains with a duration shorter than here specified (in 1/10 sek), are ignored.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputPortTable.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputPortTable
wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputPortTable.description: List of settings depending on the output number.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputPortEntry.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputPortEntry
wtWebioEA2x2_24VOutputPortEntry.description: Output parameters of the individual outputs.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortOutputGroupMode.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortOutputGroupMode
wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortOutputGroupMode.description: It is possible to connect outputs together to increase the output current. This could be done by connecting 2 or 4 outputs in a group together. All bits of such a group has to be set all together in the same way. This variable configures this group scheme. If one ouput bit of a group is set, all other output bits of the same group will be set in the same manner. More than one configuration must not be selected. Selection for ouputs 0-1: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0 : ouputs 0,1 disconnected (default) Bit 1 : ouputs 0+1 connected

wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortOutputSafetyState.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortOutputSafetyState
wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortOutputSafetyState.description: This variable allows setting of individual digital outputs. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. The first four OCTETS contain the mask which determines which of the outputs are to be set (corresponding bit = 1) and which outputs are to remain unchanged (corresponding bit = 0): OCTET 1 : unused OCTET 2 : unused OCTET 3 : unused OCTET 4, Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Mask for digital output OCTETS 5-8 contain the level (1=HIGH, 0=LOW) which the outputs to be changed should assume: OCTET 5 : unused OCTET 6 : unused OCTET 7 : unused OCTET 8, Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Level of digital output

wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortLogicInputMask.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortLogicInputMask
wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortLogicInputMask.description: Selecting one of these inputs by setting the corresponding bit to 1 enables the logic function for the output identified by the index within this table. The calculation take place in 4 steps: 1. Selecting inputs (wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortLogicInputMask) 2. Inverting inputs if necessary (wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortLogicInputInverter) 3. Logical combination (wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortLogicFunction) 4. Inverting the result if necessary (wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortLogicOutputInverter) OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0-1 : inputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortLogicInputInverter.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortLogicInputInverter
wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortLogicInputInverter.description: Every input bit selected here will be inverted. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0-1 : inputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortLogicFunction.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortLogicFunction
wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortLogicFunction.description: This determines the logic function. No more than one function may be selected. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0 : logic function OR (default) Bit 1 : logic function AND Bit 2-7 : unused

wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortLogicOutputInverter.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortLogicOutputInverter
wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortLogicOutputInverter.description: The logical operation result could be inverteted by setting the corresponding bit to 1. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0 : Output Inverter enable Bit 1-7 : unused

wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortPulseDuration.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortPulseDuration
wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortPulseDuration.description: Pulse length in 1/1000 sec. Setting this value to zero, disables the pulse output.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortPulsePolarity.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortPulsePolarity
wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortPulsePolarity.description: This value defines the polarity of the output pulse, if wtWebioEA2x2_24VPortPulseDuration is not set to zero. After the pulse is finished, the output switches back to the opposite state. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0 : negative polarity Bit 1 : positive polarity Bit 2-7 : unused

wtWebioEA2x2_24VDiagErrorCount.description: Number of entries in the error memory.

wtWebioEA2x2_24VDiagErrorClear.name: wtWebioEA2x2_24VDiagErrorClear

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VInputState.description: Value of a single input bit.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VInputValue.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VInputValue
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VInputValue.description: This variable is used to read the inputs of the digital I/O port. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Digital outputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VOutputState.description: Value of a single output bit.

The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Digital outputs 0-1 Bit 2-7: ungenutzt

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VSetOutput.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VSetOutput
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VSetOutput.description: This variable allows setting of individual digital outputs. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. The first two OCTETS contain the mask which determines which of the outputs are to be set (corresponding bit = 1) and which outputs are to remain unchanged (corresponding bit = 0): OCTET 1 : unused OCTET 2 : unused OCTET 3 : unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Mask for digital outputs 0-1 OCTETS 5-8 contain the level (1=HIGH, 0=LOW) which the outputs should assume: OCTET 5 : unused OCTET 6 : unused OCTET 7 : unused OCTET 8, Bit 0-1: Level of digital outputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VSessCntrlConfigMode.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VSessCntrlConfigMode
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VSessCntrlConfigMode.description: When the device is in SNMP configuration mode, the value 1 is returned, otherwise 0. If the read value is 0 even though the password was written, the device is already in config mode and the variables can only be read.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VSessCntrlLogout.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VSessCntrlLogout
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VSessCntrlLogout.description: If the device is in configuration mode and the session was opened by this SNMP Manager, writing a 1 to this variable will end the session and all parameters are stored. Writing a 2 discards all entries again. When read this variable provides the value 0.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VSessCntrlAdminPasswor.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VSessCntrlAdminPassword
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VSessCntrlAdminPasswor.description: This password protects access to the variables with administrator rights. It can only be changed by the administrator. If no password was assigned, the valid password is public.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VSessCntrlConfigPasswo.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VSessCntrlConfigPassword

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VGetHeaderEnable.description: If bits are set, every answer of a short form GET question will be lead by the IP-address and name of the device (Header) or a HTTP header (HTTP): Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 2-7: unused Bit 1 : GET HTTP enable Bit 0 : GET Header enable

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VHttpInputTrigger.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VHttpInputTrigger
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VHttpInputTrigger.description: Every change on the inputs causes their state to be transmitted to the remote device. To minimize data traffic, individual inputs may be exempted from this rule. Nevertheless every transmission will contain all input bits. If a bit is set (1), a change of state on the corresponding input triggers a transmission. If the bit is not set (0), no transmission takes place. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Digital inputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VHttpPort.description: Definition of the standard HTML port (Default: 80).

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VMailAuthentication.description: Selection of the authentication modi: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. Bit 1 decided wether the community string of read operations is compared with the system password or not: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : SNMP enable

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VUdpEnable.description: Set this bit to enable UDP support: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : UDP enable

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryOperationMode.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryOperationMode
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryOperationMode.description: Selection of the operation mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : UDP Peer Bit 1 : TCP Client Bit 0 : TCP Server

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpServerLocalP.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpServerLocalPort
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpServerLocalP.description: Local TCP port for data exchange in this server mode. This port number must be unique within the device. Reserved port number must not be used (refere to the manual).

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpServerInputT.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpServerInputTrigger
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpServerInputT.description: Every change on the inputs causes their state to be transmitted to the remote device. To minimize data traffic, individual inputs may be exempted from this rule. Nevertheless every transmission will contain all input bits. If a bit is set (1), a change of state on the corresponding input triggers a transmission. If the bit is not set (0), no transmission takes place. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Digital inputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpServerApplic.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpServerApplicationMode
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpServerApplic.description: Selection of the application mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 4-7: unused Bit 3 : OPC Device Bit 2 : Box2Box Slave Bit 1 : Compatible 50xxx Bit 0 : Default

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpClientLocalP.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpClientLocalPort
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpClientLocalP.description: Local TCP port for data exchange in this client mode. This port number must be unique within the device. Reserved port number must not be used (refere to the manual).

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpClientServer.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpClientServerPort
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpClientServer.description: Port number of the server. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the server port to zero.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpClientServer.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpClientServerIpAddr
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpClientServer.description: Ip address of the server. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the server IP address to 0.0.0.0.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpClientServer.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpClientServerPassword
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpClientServer.description: Building a connection may be protected by the administrator password of the server. Enter the server password to establish the connection, if a server administrator password exists.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpClientInacti.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpClientInactivity
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpClientInacti.description: Connection timeout in 100ms. If no data are exchanged within the specified time, the device closes the connection to the server. The value 0 deactivates the timer. Using the Box2Box mode this function is disabled.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpClientInterv.description: Configurable interval with a 100ms base, in which the Webio device sends data to the configured application. A interval of zero stopps the periodical sending.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpClientApplic.description: Selection of the application mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : Box2Box Slave Bit 1 : Compatible 50xxx Bit 0 : Default

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryUdpPeerRemoteIp.description: Ip address of the remote device. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the remote device IP address to 0.0.0.0.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VBinaryTcpClientServer.description: HTTP port number of the remote device at TCP Client Mode. In the operating mode Box2Box connection status informations will be exchanged through this port.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VSyslogSystemMessagesE.description: Binary coded trigger conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: ColdStart Bit 1: WarmStart Bit 2: Diag Messages Bit 3-7: unused

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VSyslogEnable.description: Set bit 0to enable Syslog: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Syslog enable

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VFTPServerControlPort.description: Portnumber of the control port of the FTP server, default 21.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VFTPOption.description: Bit 0 switches the FTP Server in Passiv-Mode, the Client controls the data connection on its own: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : PASV enable

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VWayBackEnable.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VWayBackEnable
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VWayBackEnable.description: Set Bit 0 to enable WayBack: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : WayBack enable

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VWayBackServerControlP.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VWayBackServerControlPort
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VWayBackServerControlP.description: Portnumber of the control port of the FTP server, default 21.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VWayBackFTPPassword.description: WayBack FTP Loggin: Password of the user.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VWayBackFTPResponse.description: WayBack FTP response: return message after login.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VWayBackFTPTimeOut.description: WayBack FTP Timeout: a request must be finished within this periode of time.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VOutputModeTable.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VOutputModeTable
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VOutputModeTable.description: Table of output mode configurations dependent on the output indices.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VOutputModeEntry.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VOutputModeEntry
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VOutputModeEntry.description: Output mode configurations of the individual outputs.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VOutputModeBit.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VOutputModeBit
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VOutputModeBit.description: This binary coded output mode defines the individual operation mode for any output. More than one mode must not be selected. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 6-7: unused Bit 5 : Logic Bit 4 : Binary 2 Bit 3 : Binary 1 Bit 2 : SNMP Bit 1 : UDP ASCII Bit 0 : HTTP

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VSafetyTimeout.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VSafetyTimeout
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VSafetyTimeout.description: After this period of time (multiple of 100ms) without receiving data outputs switch to their Safety States. For each output a independend safety state could be defined.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VLoadControlEnable.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VLoadControlEnable
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VLoadControlEnable.description: Here the function of automatic load control can be enabled. All output were tested in pairs (0-1). If an error occours at one output, both output of an pair will be switched of. For a properly function of the load control each output of a pair have to has a load. If there is no existing load, a pull down resistor can be used. Outputs with no load are automaticly detected and not part of the control function. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Load Control enable

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPowerSupplyEnable.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPowerSupplyEnable
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPowerSupplyEnable.description: Setting this enable bit turns on the intarnal 24V power supply of the outputs. All currents out must not exceed 150mA. At overcurrent condition the power supply will be shut down automatically. To reset the ocvercurrent protection circuit write 1 into wtWebioEA2x2DiagErrorClear. Internal power supply is a feature of 57638 only. Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Power Supply enable

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmTable.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmTable
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmTable.description: List of settings depending on the alarm number.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmEntry.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmEntry
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmEntry.description: Alarm parameters of the individual alarms.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmInputTrigger.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmInputTrigger
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmInputTrigger.description: This variable allows setting of individual input trigger conditions. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. The first four OCTETS contain the mask which determines which of the inputs are to be considered (corresponding bit = 1) and which inputs are to ignore (corresponding bit = 0): OCTET 1 : unused OCTET 2 : unused OCTET 3 : unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Mask for digital inputs 0-1 OCTETS 5-8 contain the level (1=HIGH, 0=LOW) which the inputs should assume: OCTET 5 : unused OCTET 6 : unused OCTET 7 : unused OCTET 8, Bit 0-1: Level of digital inputs 0-1 OCTETS 9-12 contain the ANY bit (1=ON, 0=OFF). Inputs masked with the any bit trigger with any change of the corresponding input bit. Settings in OCTET 5-9 are then unused: OCTET 9: unused OCTET 10: unused OCTET 11: unused OCTET 12, Bit 0-1: ANY bits of digital inputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmOutputTrigger.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmOutputTrigger
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmOutputTrigger.description: This variable allows setting of individual output trigger conditions. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. The first four OCTETS contain the mask which determines which of the outputs are to be considered (corresponding bit = 1) and which outputs are to ignore (corresponding bit = 0): OCTET 1 : unused OCTET 2 : unused OCTET 3 : unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Mask for digital outputs 0-1 OCTETS 5-8 contain the level (1=HIGH, 0=LOW) which the outputs should assume: OCTET 5 : unused OCTET 6 : unused OCTET 7 : unused OCTET 8, Bit 0-1: Level of digital outputs 0-1 OCTETS 9-12 contain the ANY bit (1=ON, 0=OFF). Outputs masked with the any bit trigger with any change of the corresponding output bit. Settings in OCTET 5-9 are then unused: OCTET 9: unused OCTET 10: unused OCTET 11: unused OCTET 12, Bit 0-1: ANY bits of digital outputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmSystemTrigger.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmSystemTrigger
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmSystemTrigger.description: Binary coded trigger conditions: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 4-7: unused Bit 3 : Warm Start Bit 2 : Cold Start Bit 1 : Timer Bit 0 : Load Control

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmMaxCounterValue.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmMaxCounterValue
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmMaxCounterValue.description: This variable configures a max. counter value. If an input counter value exceeds this max. value, the corresponding alarm is triggered. Input counters with its mask bit unset in wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmInputTrigger are not considered.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmEnable.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmEnable
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmEnable.description: Binary coded alarm enable: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: Mail Enable Bit 1: SNMP Trap enable Bit 2: UDP enable Bit 3: Send inputs to pending TCP connections Bit 4: TCP Client enable Bit 5: Syslog Messages enable Bit 6-7: unused

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmMailAddr.description: E-Mail address for sending the alarm mail to.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmFtpDataPort.description: Local data port: 1..65535 or AUTO: the next free port will be assigned.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmFtpFileName.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmFtpFileName
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmFtpFileName.description: Name of the file including path informations.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmFtpText.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmFtpText
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmFtpText.description: Message text to store on the FTP server.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmFtpOption.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmFtpOption
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmFtpOption.description: Binary coded options, select only one option at the same time: STORE = replace file APPEND = append message at the end of the file Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0 : STORE Bit 1 : APPEND Bit 2-7: unused

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmTimerCron.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmTimerCron
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmTimerCron.description: This entry contains 5 space or tab seperated text fields for time trigger definition. Each field must match with the actual time to trigger a message, weekday and day of month are interpreted separatley. 1: Minutes Range 0-59 2. Hours Range 0-23, 0 is midnight 3: Day of month Range 1-31 4: Month Range 1-12 5: Weekday Range 0-6, 0 is sunday Syntax for every field: - an asterix (*) enables every possible setting of a field - single numbers seperated by commas - a partition within the allowed range (1-5) - step size within an partition of the allowed range (0-59/2: every second minute).

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmMailReleaseText.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmMailReleaseText
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmMailReleaseText.description: Release Alarm mail text: States of the Webio device can be included by using special tags. Please refer to the respective Webio manual

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmSnmpTrapReleaseT.description: This text appears in the trap body.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmSyslogReleaseTex.description: Every message starts with the priority key, a time stamp and the host ip address, according RFC3164. This text appears in the following syslog message body.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmFtpReleaseText.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VAlarmFtpReleaseText

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VLoadControlView.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VLoadControlView
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VLoadControlView.description: Here the result of automatic load control can be read. All output were tested in pairs (0-1). If an error occours at one output, both output of an pair will be switched of. For a properly function of the load control each output of a pair have to has a load. If there is no existing load, a pull down resistor can be used. Outputs with no load are automaticly detected and not part of the control function. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0-1: outputs 0-1.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VLCShutDownView.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VLCShutDownView
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VLCShutDownView.description: Here the result of the automatic load control shut down can be read. All outputs remain switched of, until a zero is written into this variable. But previously all loads should be inspected. High current (short circuit), a broken supply line or a defect load (i.e. lamp) may be a shut down reason. If no load is detected, the load control unit suspend automaticly the control of the corresponding output pair. All controlled output could be identified reading the variable wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VLoadControlEnable. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an ouput. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0-1: outputs 0-1.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VInputPortTable.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VInputPortTable
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VInputPortTable.description: List of settings depending on the input number.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VInputPortEntry.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VInputPortEntry
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VInputPortEntry.description: Input parameter for the individual inputs.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortInputMode.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortInputMode
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortInputMode.description: Binary coded modes: Selecting short pulse detection enable by setting the corresponding bit to 1 enables interrupt support for counting. Only positive edges are accepted as trigger source. The maximum counting frequenz equals 2000 Hz. This mode is available for inputs 0-3 only. Selecting counter clear on read by setting the corresponding bit to 1 enables the corresponding counter to be cleared automatically every time it is read, except HTTP reading with user rights. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. Selection for input 0-1: OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 4-7: unused Bit 3 : Bidirectional counter enable Bit 2 : Counter clear on read Bit 1 : Change detection enable (default) Bit 0 : Short Pulse detection enable

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortInputFilter.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortInputFilter
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortInputFilter.description: Pulses with a duration shorter than here specified (duration in 1/1000 sec), are ignored.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortInputBicountPulse.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortInputBicountPulsePolarity
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortInputBicountPulse.description: This value defines the polarity of the input pulse. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0 : negative polarity Bit 1 : positive polarity Bit 2-7 : unused

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortInputBicountInact.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortInputBicountInactivTimeout
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortInputBicountInact.description: Pulse chains with a duration shorter than here specified (in 1/10 sek), are ignored.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VOutputPortTable.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VOutputPortTable
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VOutputPortTable.description: List of settings depending on the output number.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VOutputPortEntry.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VOutputPortEntry
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VOutputPortEntry.description: Output parameters of the individual outputs.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortOutputGroupMode.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortOutputGroupMode
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortOutputGroupMode.description: It is possible to connect outputs together to increase the output current. This could be done by connecting 2 or 4 outputs in a group together. All bits of such a group has to be set all together in the same way. This variable configures this group scheme. If one ouput bit of a group is set, all other output bits of the same group will be set in the same manner. More than one configuration must not be selected. Selection for ouputs 0-1: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0 : ouputs 0,1 disconnected (default) Bit 1 : ouputs 0+1 connected

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortOutputSafetyState.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortOutputSafetyState
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortOutputSafetyState.description: This variable allows setting of individual digital outputs. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. The first four OCTETS contain the mask which determines which of the outputs are to be set (corresponding bit = 1) and which outputs are to remain unchanged (corresponding bit = 0): OCTET 1 : unused OCTET 2 : unused OCTET 3 : unused OCTET 4, Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Mask for digital output OCTETS 5-8 contain the level (1=HIGH, 0=LOW) which the outputs to be changed should assume: OCTET 5 : unused OCTET 6 : unused OCTET 7 : unused OCTET 8, Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Level of digital output

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortLogicInputMask.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortLogicInputMask
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortLogicInputMask.description: Selecting one of these inputs by setting the corresponding bit to 1 enables the logic function for the output identified by the index within this table. The calculation take place in 4 steps: 1. Selecting inputs (wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortLogicInputMask) 2. Inverting inputs if necessary (wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortLogicInputInverter) 3. Logical combination (wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortLogicFunction) 4. Inverting the result if necessary (wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortLogicOutputInverter) OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0-1 : inputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortLogicInputInverte.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortLogicInputInverter
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortLogicInputInverte.description: Every input bit selected here will be inverted. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0-1 : inputs 0-1

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortLogicFunction.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortLogicFunction
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortLogicFunction.description: This determines the logic function. No more than one function may be selected. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0 : logic function OR (default) Bit 1 : logic function AND Bit 2-7 : unused

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortLogicOutputInvert.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortLogicOutputInverter
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortLogicOutputInvert.description: The logical operation result could be inverteted by setting the corresponding bit to 1. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0 : Output Inverter enable Bit 1-7 : unused

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortPulseDuration.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortPulseDuration
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortPulseDuration.description: Pulse length in 1/1000 sec. Setting this value to zero, disables the pulse output.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortPulsePolarity.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortPulsePolarity
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortPulsePolarity.description: This value defines the polarity of the output pulse, if wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VPortPulseDuration is not set to zero. After the pulse is finished, the output switches back to the opposite state. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0 : negative polarity Bit 1 : positive polarity Bit 2-7 : unused

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VDiagErrorCount.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VDiagErrorCount
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VDiagErrorCount.description: Number of entries in the error memory.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VDiagErrorIndex.description: The value of this variable is used as an index to read an error massege from wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VDiagErrorMessage. Errors are numbered from 1 to wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VDiagErrorCount. Writing a valid value into this variable, making the appropriate message readable from wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VDiagErrorMessage.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VDiagErrorMessage.name: wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VDiagErrorMessage
wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VDiagErrorMessage.description: Using wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VDiagErrorIndex as an index, the appropriate message is available.

wtWebioEA2x2ERP_24VDiagErrorClear.description: Writing 1 into this variable clears all diagnosis messages.

wtIpWatcher_24VInputValue.description: This variable is used to read the inputs of the digital I/O port. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Digital outputs 0-1

wtIpWatcher_24VOutputState.description: Value of a single output bit.

wtIpWatcher_24VOutputValue.description: This variable is used to read and write the outputs of the digital I/O port. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Digital outputs 0-1 Bit 2-7: ungenutzt

wtIpWatcher_24VSetOutput.name: wtIpWatcher_24VSetOutput
wtIpWatcher_24VSetOutput.description: This variable allows setting of individual digital outputs. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. The first two OCTETS contain the mask which determines which of the outputs are to be set (corresponding bit = 1) and which outputs are to remain unchanged (corresponding bit = 0): OCTET 1 : unused OCTET 2 : unused OCTET 3 : unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Mask for digital outputs 0-1 OCTETS 5-8 contain the level (1=HIGH, 0=LOW) which the outputs should assume: OCTET 5 : unused OCTET 6 : unused OCTET 7 : unused OCTET 8, Bit 0-1: Level of digital outputs 0-1

wtIpWatcher_24VSessCntrlPassword.name: wtIpWatcher_24VSessCntrlPassword
wtIpWatcher_24VSessCntrlPassword.description: Entering this password opens a session which is ended by writing a 1 to wtIpWatcher_24VSessCntrlLogout. When read this variable provides a string of length zero.

wtIpWatcher_24VSessCntrlConfigMode.name: wtIpWatcher_24VSessCntrlConfigMode
wtIpWatcher_24VSessCntrlConfigMode.description: When the device is in SNMP configuration mode, the value 1 is returned, otherwise 0. If the read value is 0 even though the password was written, the device is already in config mode and the variables can only be read.

wtIpWatcher_24VSessCntrlLogout.name: wtIpWatcher_24VSessCntrlLogout
wtIpWatcher_24VSessCntrlLogout.description: If the device is in configuration mode and the session was opened by this SNMP Manager, writing a 1 to this variable will end the session and all parameters are stored. Writing a 2 discards all entries again. When read this variable provides the value 0.

wtIpWatcher_24VSessCntrlAdminPassword.name: wtIpWatcher_24VSessCntrlAdminPassword
wtIpWatcher_24VSessCntrlAdminPassword.description: This password protects access to the variables with administrator rights. It can only be changed by the administrator. If no password was assigned, the valid password is public.

wtIpWatcher_24VSessCntrlConfigPassword.name: wtIpWatcher_24VSessCntrlConfigPassword
wtIpWatcher_24VSessCntrlConfigPassword.description: This password protects access to the variables with configurator rights. It can be changed by the administrator and by the configurator. If no password was assigned, the valid password is public. When read this variable provides a null-pointer.

wtIpWatcher_24VUdpRemotePort.description: Udp remote port setting. If this value is set to zero, the source port read from a request will be used as destination port for the answer. A non zero value forced the destination port to this value.

wtIpWatcher_24VSyslogServerIP.name: wtIpWatcher_24VSyslogServerIP
wtIpWatcher_24VSyslogServerIP.description: Name or IP address of the Syslog server, which accepts the Syslog messgaes.

wtIpWatcher_24VSyslogSystemMessagesEnabl.description: Binary coded trigger conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: ColdStart Bit 1: WarmStart Bit 2: Diag Messages Bit 3-7: unused

wtIpWatcher_24VSyslogEnable.name: wtIpWatcher_24VSyslogEnable
wtIpWatcher_24VSyslogEnable.description: Set bit 0to enable Syslog: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Syslog enable

wtIpWatcher_24VFTPServerIP.name: wtIpWatcher_24VFTPServerIP
wtIpWatcher_24VFTPServerIP.description: Name or IP address of the FTP server, which accepts the FTP messages.

wtIpWatcher_24VFTPServerControlPort.name: wtIpWatcher_24VFTPServerControlPort
wtIpWatcher_24VFTPServerControlPort.description: Portnumber of the control port of the FTP server, default 21.

wtIpWatcher_24VFTPOption.name: wtIpWatcher_24VFTPOption
wtIpWatcher_24VFTPOption.description: Bit 0 switches the FTP Server in Passiv-Mode, the Client controls the data connection on its own: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : PASV enable

wtIpWatcher_24VFTPEnable.name: wtIpWatcher_24VFTPEnable
wtIpWatcher_24VFTPEnable.description: Set Bit 0 to enable FTP: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : FTP enable

wtIpWatcher_24VIpListPort.name: wtIpWatcher_24VIpListPort
wtIpWatcher_24VIpListPort.description: Port number, zero in the case of broadcast or Ping.

wtIpWatcher_24VIpListService.name: wtIpWatcher_24VIpListService
wtIpWatcher_24VIpListService.description: Binary coded scan mode, only one mode can be selected at a particular time: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: Ping enable Bit 1-7: unused

wtIpWatcher_24VIpListEnable.name: wtIpWatcher_24VIpListEnable
wtIpWatcher_24VIpListEnable.description: Binary coded alarm enable: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: enabled in Alarm 1 Bit 1: enabled in Alarm 2 Bit 2: enabled in Alarm 3 Bit 3: enabled in Alarm 4 Bit 4-7: unused

wtIpWatcher_24VPowerSupplyEnable.name: wtIpWatcher_24VPowerSupplyEnable
wtIpWatcher_24VPowerSupplyEnable.description: Setting this enable bit turns on the intarnal 24V power supply of the outputs. All currents out must not exceed 150mA. At overcurrent condition the power supply will be shut down automatically. To reset the ocvercurrent protection circuit write 1 into wtIpWatcher_24VDiagErrorClear. Internal power supply is a feature of 57655 only. Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Power Supply enable

wtIpWatcher_24VAlarmTable.description: List of settings depending on the alarm number.

wtIpWatcher_24VAlarmEntry.description: Alarm parameters of the individual alarms.

wtIpWatcher_24VAlarmEnable.name: wtIpWatcher_24VAlarmEnable
wtIpWatcher_24VAlarmEnable.description: Binary coded alarm enable: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: Mail Enable Bit 1: SNMP Trap enable Bit 2: UDP enable Bit 3: Send inputs to pending TCP connections Bit 4: TCP Client enable Bit 5: Syslog Messages enable Bit 6-7: unused

wtIpWatcher_24VAlarmFtpDataPort.name: wtIpWatcher_24VAlarmFtpDataPort
wtIpWatcher_24VAlarmFtpDataPort.description: Local data port: 1..65535 or AUTO: the next free port will be assigned.

wtIpWatcher_24VAlarmFtpOption.name: wtIpWatcher_24VAlarmFtpOption
wtIpWatcher_24VAlarmFtpOption.description: Binary coded options, select only one option at the same time: STORE = replace file APPEND = append message at the end of the file Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0 : STORE Bit 1 : APPEND Bit 2-7: unused

wtIpWatcher_24VAlarmTimerCron.name: wtIpWatcher_24VAlarmTimerCron
wtIpWatcher_24VAlarmTimerCron.description: This entry contains 5 space or tab seperated text fields for time trigger definition. Each field must match with the actual time to trigger a message, weekday and day of month are interpreted separatley. 1: Minutes Range 0-59 2. Hours Range 0-23, 0 is midnight 3: Day of month Range 1-31 4: Month Range 1-12 5: Weekday Range 0-6, 0 is sunday Syntax for every field: - an asterix (*) enables every possible setting of a field - single numbers seperated by commas - a partition within the allowed range (1-5) - step size within an partition of the allowed range (0-59/2: every second minute).

wtTrapReceiver2x2SystemTimerNo.description: Index number of the system timer.

wtTrapReceiver2x2SessCntrlPassword.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2SessCntrlPassword
wtTrapReceiver2x2SessCntrlPassword.description: Entering this password opens a session which is ended by writing a 1 to wtTrapReceiver2x2SessCntrlLogout. When read this variable provides a string of length zero.

wtTrapReceiver2x2SessCntrlConfigMode.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2SessCntrlConfigMode
wtTrapReceiver2x2SessCntrlConfigMode.description: When the device is in SNMP configuration mode, the value 1 is returned, otherwise 0. If the read value is 0 even though the password was written, the device is already in config mode and the variables can only be read.

wtTrapReceiver2x2SessCntrlLogout.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2SessCntrlLogout
wtTrapReceiver2x2SessCntrlLogout.description: If the device is in configuration mode and the session was opened by this SNMP Manager, writing a 1 to this variable will end the session and all parameters are stored. Writing a 2 discards all entries again. When read this variable provides the value 0.

wtTrapReceiver2x2SessCntrlAdminPassword.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2SessCntrlAdminPassword
wtTrapReceiver2x2SessCntrlAdminPassword.description: This password protects access to the variables with administrator rights. It can only be changed by the administrator. If no password was assigned, the valid password is public.

wtTrapReceiver2x2SessCntrlConfigPassword.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2SessCntrlConfigPassword
wtTrapReceiver2x2SessCntrlConfigPassword.description: This password protects access to the variables with configurator rights. It can be changed by the administrator and by the configurator. If no password was assigned, the valid password is public. When read this variable provides a null-pointer.

wtTrapReceiver2x2StTzStopMin.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2StTzStopMin

wtTrapReceiver2x2MailEnable.description: Set this bit to enable the sending of mails: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Mail enable

wtTrapReceiver2x2MailAuthentication.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2MailAuthentication
wtTrapReceiver2x2MailAuthentication.description: Selection of the authentication modi: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. wtTrapReceiver2x2MailPop3Server.description: Name or Ip-address of the POP3 Servers.

wtTrapReceiver2x2SnmpEnable.description: Set bit 0 to enable SNMP. If disabled, the device did not respond to any SNMP requests. Bit 1 decided wether the community string of read operations is compared with the system password or not: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : SNMP enable

wtTrapReceiver2x2SnmpSystemTrapManagerIP.description: Name or IP address of the TCP server which accepts the system trap.

wtTrapReceiver2x2SnmpSystemTrapEnable.description: Binary coded trigger conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: ColdStart Bit 1: WarmStart Bit 2: Diag messages Bit 3-7: unused

wtTrapReceiver2x2UdpAdminPort.description: Udp port to which the Udp queries ( short form GET requests) can be sent. This port number must be unique within the device.

wtTrapReceiver2x2UdpEnable.description: Set this bit to enable UDP support: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : UDP enable

wtTrapReceiver2x2UdpRemotePort.description: Udp remote port setting. If this value is set to zero, the source port read from a request will be used as destination port for the answer. A non zero value forced the destination port to this value.

wtTrapReceiver2x2SyslogEnable.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2SyslogEnable
wtTrapReceiver2x2SyslogEnable.description: Set bit 0to enable Syslog: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Syslog enable

wtTrapReceiver2x2FTPEnable.description: Set Bit 0 to enable FTP: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : FTP enable

wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListPort.description: Port number, zero in the case of broadcast or Ping.

wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListService.description: Binary coded scan mode, only one mode can be selected at a particular time: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: unused Bit 1: unused Bit 2: SNMP Trap reveive enable Bit 3: Syslog receive enable Bit 4-7: unused

wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListEnable.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListEnable
wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListEnable.description: Binary coded alarm enable: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: Bit 0: enabled in Report 9 Bit 1: enabled in Report 10 Bit 2: enabled in Report 11 Bit 3: enabled in Report 12 Bit 4-7: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: enabled in Report 1 Bit 1: enabled in Report 2 Bit 2: enabled in Report 3 Bit 3: enabled in Report 4 Bit 4: enabled in Report 5 Bit 5: enabled in Report 6 Bit 6: enabled in Report 7 Bit 7: enabled in Report 8

wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListTrapNo.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListTrapNo
wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListTrapNo.description: SNMP Trap No: this filter is only active, if SNMP Trap reveive enable in wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListService is set.

wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListSpecificNo.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListSpecificNo
wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListSpecificNo.description: SNMP Specific No: this filter is only active, if SNMP Trap reveive enable in wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListService is set.

wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListFacility.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListFacility
wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListFacility.description: Syslog message level Facility: this filter is only active, if Syslog receive enable in wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListService is set.

wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListSeverity.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListSeverity
wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListSeverity.description: Syslog message level Severity: this filter is only active, if Syslog receive enable in wtTrapReceiver2x2WatchListService is set.

wtTrapReceiver2x2PowerSupplyEnable.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2PowerSupplyEnable
wtTrapReceiver2x2PowerSupplyEnable.description: Setting this enable bit turns on the intarnal 24V power supply of the outputs. All currents out must not exceed 150mA. At overcurrent condition the power supply will be shut down automatically. To reset the ocvercurrent protection circuit write 1 into wtTrapReceiver2x2DiagErrorClear. Internal power supply is a feature of 57655 only. Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Power Supply enable

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionTable.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionTable
wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionTable.description: List of settings depending on the alarm number.

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionEntry.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionEntry
wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionEntry.description: Action parameters of the individual alarms.

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionInputTrigger.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionInputTrigger
wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionInputTrigger.description: This variable allows setting of individual input trigger conditions. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. The four OCTETS contain the mask which determines which of the inputs are to be considered (corresponding bit = 1) and which inputs are to ignore (corresponding bit = 0): OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0: Input 0 falling edge Bit 1: Input 0 rising edge Bit 2: Input 1 falling edge Bit 3: Input 1 rising edge Bit 4-7: unused

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionEnable.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionEnable
wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionEnable.description: Binary coded alarm enable: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: Mail Enable Bit 1: SNMP Trap enable Bit 2: UDP enable Bit 3: Send inputs to pending TCP connections Bit 4: TCP Client enable Bit 5: Syslog Messages enable Bit 6-7: unused

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionMailAddr.description: E-Mail address for sending the alarm mail to.

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionMailText.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionMailText
wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionMailText.description: Action mail text: States of the Webio device can be included by using special tags. Please refer to the respective Webio manual

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionSnmpManagerIP.description: IP address of the SNMP Manager to which the Webio device should send SNMP traps.

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionSnmpTrapText.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionSnmpTrapText
wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionSnmpTrapText.description: This text appears in the trap body.

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionUdpIpAddr.description: IP address of the UDP listener to which the Webio device should send UDP traps.

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionUdpPort.description: Port number of the UDP listener to which the Webio device should send UDP traps.

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionUdpText.description: This text appears in the UDP trap body.

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionTcpIpAddr.description: IP address of the TCP listener to which the Webio device should send TCP traps.

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionTcpPort.description: Port number of the TCP listener to which the Webio device should send TCP traps.

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionTcpText.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionTcpText
wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionTcpText.description: This text appears in the TCP trap body.

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionSyslogIpAddr.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionSyslogIpAddr
wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionSyslogIpAddr.description: IP address of the syslog server to which the Webio device should send syslog messages.

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionSyslogPort.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionSyslogPort
wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionSyslogPort.description: Port number of the syslog server to which the Webio device should send syslog messages.

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionSyslogText.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionSyslogText
wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionSyslogText.description: Every message starts with the priority key, a time stamp and the host ip address, according RFC3164. This text appears in the following syslog message body.

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionFtpDataPort.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionFtpDataPort
wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionFtpDataPort.description: Local data port: 1..65535 or AUTO: the next free port will be assigned.

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionFtpFileName.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionFtpFileName
wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionFtpFileName.description: Name of the file including path informations.

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionFtpText.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionFtpText
wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionFtpText.description: Message text to store on the FTP server.

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionFtpOption.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionFtpOption
wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionFtpOption.description: Binary coded options, select only one option at the same time: STORE = replace file APPEND = append message at the end of the file Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0 : STORE Bit 1 : APPEND Bit 2-7: unused

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionTimerCron.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionTimerCron
wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionTimerCron.description: This entry contains 10 space or tab seperated text fields defining a time window for sending time triggered messages. 2 CRON time for start time and stop time are defined as follows: Start time: field 1: Minutes Range 0-59 3. Hours Range 0-23, 0 is midnight 5: Day of month Range 1-31 7: Month Range 1-12 9: Weekday Range 0-6, 0 is sunday Stop time: field 2: Minutes Range 0-59 4. Hours Range 0-23, 0 is midnight 6: Day of month Range 1-31 8: Month Range 1-12 10: Weekday Range 0-6, 0 is sunday Syntax for every field: - an asterix (*) enables every possible setting of a field - single numbers seperated by commas - a partition within the allowed range (1-5) - step size within an partition of the allowed range (0-59/2: every second minute).

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionGlobalEnable.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionGlobalEnable
wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionGlobalEnable.description: Binary coded alarm activation: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Action enable

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionSystemTimerTrigge.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionSystemTimerTrigger
wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionSystemTimerTrigge.description: Binary coded system timer activation: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0: System Timer 1 enable Bit 1: System Timer 2 enable Bit 2-7: unused

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionSystemButtonTrigg.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionSystemButtonTrigger
wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionSystemButtonTrigg.description: Binary coded button activation: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0: Button 1 enable Bit 1: Button 2 enable Bit 2: Button 3 enable Bit 3: Button 4 enable Bit 3: Button 5 enable Bit 3: Button 6 enable Bit 3: Button 7 enable Bit 3: Button 8 enable.

wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionOutputAction.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionOutputAction
wtTrapReceiver2x2ActionOutputAction.description: This variable allows setting of individual output. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. The first four OCTETS contain the mask which determines which of the outputs are to be considered (corresponding bit = 1) and which outputs are to ignore (corresponding bit = 0): OCTET 1 : unused OCTET 2 : unused OCTET 3 : unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Mask for digital outputs 0-1 OCTETS 5-8 contain the level (1=HIGH, 0=LOW) which the outputs should assume: OCTET 5 : unused OCTET 6 : unused OCTET 7 : unused OCTET 8, Bit 0-1: Level of digital outputs 0-1 OCTETS 9-12 contain the TOOGLE bit (1=ON, 0=OFF). outputs masked with the TOGGLE bit trigger change their state on every action. Settings in OCTET 5-9 are then unused: OCTET 9: unused OCTET 10: unused OCTET 11: unused OCTET 12, Bit 0-1: TOGGLE bits of digital outputs 0-1

wtTrapReceiver2x2SystemTimerPortTable.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2SystemTimerPortTable
wtTrapReceiver2x2SystemTimerPortTable.description: List of settings depending on the SystemTimer number.

wtTrapReceiver2x2SystemTimerPortEntry.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2SystemTimerPortEntry
wtTrapReceiver2x2SystemTimerPortEntry.description: SystemTimer parameter for the individual SystemTimer.

wtTrapReceiver2x2PortSystemTimerEnable.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2PortSystemTimerEnable
wtTrapReceiver2x2PortSystemTimerEnable.description: Binary coded SystemTimer enable: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: ungenutzt OCTET 2: ungenutzt OCTET 3: ungenutzt OCTET 4, Bit 1-7: ungenutzt Bit 0 : SystemTimer enable

wtTrapReceiver2x2PortSystemTimerCron.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2PortSystemTimerCron
wtTrapReceiver2x2PortSystemTimerCron.description: This entry contains 5 space or tab seperated text fields for time trigger definition. Each field must match with the actual time to trigger a message, weekday and day of month are interpreted separatley. 1: Minutes Range 0-59 2. Hours Range 0-23, 0 is midnight 3: Day of month Range 1-31 4: Month Range 1-12 5: Weekday Range 0-6, 0 is sunday Syntax for every field: - an asterix (*) enables every possible setting of a field - single numbers seperated by commas - a partition within the allowed range (1-5) - step size within an partition of the allowed range (0-59/2: every second minute).

wtTrapReceiver2x2ButtonPortTable.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ButtonPortTable
wtTrapReceiver2x2ButtonPortTable.description: List of settings depending on the button number.

wtTrapReceiver2x2ButtonPortEntry.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2ButtonPortEntry
wtTrapReceiver2x2ButtonPortEntry.description: Button parameter for the individual buttons.

wtTrapReceiver2x2PortButtonEnable.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2PortButtonEnable
wtTrapReceiver2x2PortButtonEnable.description: Binary coded button enable: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: ungenutzt OCTET 2: ungenutzt OCTET 3: ungenutzt OCTET 4, Bit 1-7: ungenutzt Bit 0 : Button enable

wtTrapReceiver2x2PortButtonAccess.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2PortButtonAccess
wtTrapReceiver2x2PortButtonAccess.description: Binary coded button access level: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : For user administrator visible and operable Bit 1 : For user operator visible and operable Bit 0 : For user guest visible and operable

wtTrapReceiver2x2InputPortTable.description: List of settings depending on the input number.

wtTrapReceiver2x2OutputPortTable.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2OutputPortTable
wtTrapReceiver2x2OutputPortTable.description: List of settings depending on the output number.

wtTrapReceiver2x2OutputPortEntry.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2OutputPortEntry

wtTrapReceiver2x2PortPulsePolarity.name: wtTrapReceiver2x2PortPulsePolarity
wtTrapReceiver2x2PortPulsePolarity.description: This value defines the polarity of the output pulse, if wtTrapReceiver2x2PortPulseDuration is not set to zero. After the pulse is finished, the output switches back to the opposite state. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 0 : negative polarity Bit 1 : positive polarity Bit 2-7 : unused
